INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200105, '0685792f-24aa-4a5f-8826-93ab9ebeae78', 'market for sound insulation, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical | sound insulation, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''sound insulation, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This isan immobile infrastructure, representing the production of a sound insulation, that is used in a heat and power co-generation unit with a capacity of 160kW. The dimensions of the sound insulation are width*height*depth = 5.3;m*2.5 m*2 m, and it weighs 2400 kg. A weight proportion of metal of 80% and mineral wool of 20% is assumed. The infrastructure has an assumed lifetime of 100,000 h. The process includes the most important materials used for production, their decommission and water needed for production. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200106, '06879b59-8306-49fc-a761-23e87cbc469e', 'market for blast furnace | blast furnace', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''blast furnace'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of blast furnace. The infrastructure is based on a medium-size plant. It has a yearly output of 1,500,000 tons and a life time of 50 years. The process includes input material, unloading and storage, blast furnace processes and casting and for administrative buildings. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200107, '06c1b119-99e0-4cf7-8703-7e1cdc0abe05', 'market for mine infrastructure, open cast, hard coal | mine infrastructure, open cast, hard coal', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''mine infrastructure, open cast, hard coal'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a mine infrastructure, open cast, hard coal. The infrastructure is assumed to have a lifetime of 40-50 years for the mine and a lifetime of 30 years for the machinery, while its lifetime capacity is 30,000,000,000 kg. The process includes machinery and equipment, electricity consumption and land use. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200108, '06eae829-de2f-4150-abbe-9c9692caf45a', 'market for sugar refinery | sugar refinery', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''sugar refinery'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a sugar refinery. The infrastructure represents a a typical sugar refinery with a production capacity of 200,000 tons sugar per year and a lifetime of a 50 years. The equivalent feed capacities vary from 1,300 kt/yr for sugar beets to 1,650 kt/yr for sugarcane. The process includes land use, building materials, their decommission but it excludes energy use for construction. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200109, '06f6d284-62f9-4d94-b48e-95b87a79bb9c', 'market for liquid manure spreading, by vacuum tanker | liquid manure spreading, by vacuum tanker', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''liquid manure spreading, by vacuum tanker'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''liquid manure spreading, by vacuum tanker'' of 1 m3. It includes use of mobile infrastructure (tractors, machinery) operating with diesel. Diesel consumption is the most crucial parameter within this service as it lineraly affects direct emissions generated through diesel combustion. Hence, a user can model the right amount of this service by using information on diesel consumption. For example: If within the user''s model diesel consumption is 0.2 kg of diesel per m3 while in this service it is 0.1 kg/m3, the user can model with 2 m3 of this service. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200110, '06f8dd0e-2723-418f-bbc9-dcaa3e46246e', 'market for methanol factory | methanol factory', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''methanol factory'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of methanol factory. The infrastructure has a yearly output of 2,700 tons methanol and a life time of 30 years. The process includes building materials, energy use for construction, land use and occupation for plant and the decommission of plant. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200111, '070285ef-c9f1-428b-8038-563be77c77ca', 'market for indium | indium', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''indium'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''indium'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''indium'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200112, '070c0c48-24ec-4edd-aa68-66c92eff3010', 'market for o-cresol | o-cresol', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''o-cresol'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;''o-cresol'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 000095-48-7. It is called ''o-cresol'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C7H8O. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure and has a crystalline form. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. On a consumer level, is used in the following products: polymers. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: polymers and coating products. This substance is used for the synthesis of other substances (use as intermediate). This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''o-cresol'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''o-cresol'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200113, '0717742b-b147-4634-871c-09f4883b9ec2', 'operation, reefer, cooling, 40-foot, high-cube, R134a as refrigerant | operation, reefer, cooling', 'This dataset represents operation of a reefer, intermodal shipping container. This datasets represents 1kg of cargo being stored in a container with a certain controlled atmosphere (temperature, humidity, air flow, etc.) for 1 day. Reefer can operate in two basic modes; cooling (temperatures between 0°C and 20°C) and freezing (temperatures between -35°C and -18°C). This dataset represents cooling.;The emissions from a transport carying the container are reported in the transport dataset.;The operation of such reefer depends heavily on type of goods being transported. This is a parametrized dataset (all parametres determining the elementary and intermediate exchanges of the activity are entered as parametres). The default parametres are set to represent average refrigerated storage. If specific cargo is being transported the parametres need to be adjusted accordingly. In general fruits, vegetables and flowers are being cooled during its transport and meat and seafood is frozen during its transport. ;The 40-foot container has a capacity of 2TEU. ;This reefer is using R134a as refrigerant. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200114, '072b8073-ff2e-46e3-ae1b-87eda77d9c17', 'market for wind power plant, 2MW, offshore, fixed parts | wind power plant, 2MW, offshore, fixed parts', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''wind power plant, 2MW, offshore, fixed parts'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a wind power plant, 2MW, offshore, fixed parts. The infrastructure represents the fixed parts of the wind turbine like the tower and the base, with a total height of 60 m, a capacity of 20MW and a lifetime of 20 years. The tower consists of steel and has a conical shape. The process includes building materials, their decommission, land use and construction efforts. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200115, '07321ee8-3277-4f0c-a3bf-0b58c0e13153', 'market for heat and power co-generation unit, 6400kW thermal, common components for heat+electricity | heat and power co-generation unit, 6400kW thermal, common components for heat+electricity', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''heat and power co-generation unit, 6400kW thermal, common components for heat+electricity'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the production of a heat and power co-generation unit, common components for heat and electricity, with a thermal output of 6,400kW. The infrastructure consists of the common components for heat electricity co-generation unit. It has a lifetime of 20 years, operation time for heat production of 2,030 h/year and for electricity production 3,500 h/year. The process includes the most important materials used for the fabrication of the cogeneration unit, energy needed for the production and the decommission of the unit. The factor of the electrical performance class is derived from the assumed total operating time of 100,000 hours divided by the service life of the components. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200116, '07495364-1dac-4cd1-a668-dd43ce1aaf49', 'market for hexamethylenediamine | hexamethylenediamine', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for hexamethylenediamine in the Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;Hexamethylenediamine is an organic substance with the CAS no.: 000124-09-4. It is called ''hexane-1,6-diamine'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C6H16N2. It is liquid or solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure as a crystalline solid or viscous liquid with a characteristic ammonia odor. It is modelled as a pure substance. There are no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: chemicals, plastic products, rubber products and textile, leather or fur. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce hexamethylenediamine within the geography of GLO. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of hexamethylenediamine to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200117, '07613cf7-5ea6-4d35-a2e1-f4622129cec6', 'market for low voltage system, for Li-ion battery | low voltage system, for Li-ion battery', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''low voltage system, for Li-ion battery'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''low voltage system, for Li-ion battery'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''low voltage system, for Li-ion battery'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200118, '076c7a5a-97e6-4ee2-9811-208804b80b0b', 'trimethyl borate production | trimethyl borate', 'This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of trimethyl borate by esterification of boric acid with methanol. It is a clear liquid and is soluble in organic solvents and dissolves in water with hydrolysis to boric acid and the methanol. Trimethyl borate (also known as methyl borate) is the boric acid ester of greatest commercial interest because it is used internally for the production of sodium borohydride (and diborane). Methyl borate azeotrope is used as a gaseous flux for brazing and welding, particularly in Europe. Although numerous patents have been issued on the use of boric acid esters as polymer additives, this application apparently has remained small unless there are proprietary uses that have not been disclosed. Application of small quantities of several derivatives as epoxy resin curing agents has continued with little measurable growth. Despite wide patent coverage, boric acid esters have not been used in any quantity for polymer stabilization. In the 1950s and 1960s boric acid esters derived from glycols were used extensively as gasoline additives. A mixture of these glycol derivatives is being manufactured;by U.S. Borax & Chemical Corp. under the trade name Biobor JF for the control of microorganisms in fuel systems containing water. This product can be used successfully in jet fuels, diesel fuels, and fuel oil systems that have water contamination.;Borate esters have also been patented for use as flame retardants for cotton batting, modifiers for the oxidation of hydrocarbons, starting materials for the preparation of trialkylboranes, such as triethylborane and triphenylborane, wood preservatives, hydraulic fluids (particularly alkylated glycol borates), and lubricants.;Due to the lack of production data, this dataset is based on estimations as well as data from a large chemical plant (Gendorf 2016).;References:;Sutter, J. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Highly Pure Chemicals. ecoinvent report No. 19. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, 2007.;Brotherton, R. J., Weber, C. J., Guibert, C. R. and Little, J. L. 2000. Boron Compounds. Ullmann''s Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry.;Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de. From the reception of boric acid and methanol at the factory gate. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the production of 1 kg of trimethyl borate. The system includes the process with the consumption of raw materials and energy, infrastructure and land use, as well as the generation of emissions to air and water.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200119, '0788ec48-abe8-4dc4-950c-76ec1090f1e2', 'treatment of residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste polyurethane, residual material landfill | residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste polyurethane', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in residual material landfill of a waste (residues) that is exclusively produced in another waste treatment. Residues are a by-product of municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of sewage sludge (with 70% water) that in turn is generated during wastewater treatment (WWT) of leachate from the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of ''waste polyurethane''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste polyurethane''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to river water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200120, '07b5170b-358b-4976-9be1-5b723c3839fe', 'market for uranium enrichment centrifuge facility | uranium enrichment centrifuge facility', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''uranium enrichment centrifuge facility'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of uranium enrichment centrifuge facility. The facility has capacity of 1,500 tons SWU (separative work unit). The process includes land use, energy (electricity, diesel, and light oil) and material requirements for the construction of the facility and decommission. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200121, '07d70ffb-2872-4575-9fb0-f99d14814c39', 'fluazifop-butyl production | fluazifop-butyl', 'This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of fluazifop-butyl. Emissions are estimated. Energy consumptions, infrastructure and transports are calculated with standard values. A yield of 95% per chemical step was assumed.;Fluazifop-butyl is an organic substance with the CAS no.: 069806-50-4. It is called ''butyl 2-[4-[5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxyphenoxy]propanoate'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C19H20F3NO4. It is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure with a pale brownish color. It is modelled as a pure substance. Fluazifop-butyl is a selective herbicide to control annual and perannial grasses. It is applied post-emergence and inhibits the plant acetyl-CoA carboxylase, which is a subunit in the chloroplasts of many plants. There are no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites.;Reference(s):;Unger T., (1996). Pesticide Synthesis Handbook, Noyes Publication.;Appleby A.P., Muller F., Carpy, S., (2011): Weed Control, in Ullmanns Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Weinheim, Wiley-VCH.;Chemiepark GENDORF, Umwelterklärung 2016, https://www.gendorf.de/Nachbarn/Umweltschutz/Industrie%20und%20Nachhaltigkeit;Chemiepark GENDORF, Umwelterklärung 2017, https://www.gendorf.de/Nachbarn/Umweltschutz/Industrie%20und%20Nachhaltigkeit;Chemiepark GENDORF, Umwelterklärung 2020, https://www.gendorf.de/Nachbarn/Umweltschutz/Industrie%20und%20Nachhaltigkeit;Hischier, R. (2005) Establishing Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals Based on Differing Data Availability (9 pp). The International Journal of Life Cycle Assessment, Volume 10, Issue 1, pp 59–67. 10.1065/lca2004.10.181.7 Cradle to gate. The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Production of fluazifop-butyl production including materials, energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200122, '07de56cd-17ca-419b-9753-07ff49a234a4', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI, waste graphical paper, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI, waste graphical paper', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in slag compartment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Bottom ash is the by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''waste graphical paper''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste graphical paper''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 100%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200123, '07ec555a-4d0e-453c-b944-2766b4ff9b1c', 'market for fish canning plant | fish canning plant', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''fish canning plant'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of fish canning plant. The activity of the plant also includes fish pre-processing and it is expressed as the installed capacity required to process 1000 kg of raw material. The infrastructrure has a production capacity of 7,673 kg and a lifespan of 40 years. The process includes all the building materials for the construction and maintenance of the plant. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200124, '07fcc1bb-c392-4da9-b512-1815313d1152', 'boron carbide production | boron carbide', 'This dataset represents the production of 1 kg boron carbide, at plant, global. The production of boron carbide by means of the reduction of boric oxide is considered. All data in the present report are referred to 1 kg boron carbide 100%. The system includes the process with consumption of raw materials, energy, infrastructure and land use as well as the generation of emissions to air. As no process water is used no emissions to water are assumed.It also includes transportation of the raw materials. Transient or unstable operations like starting-up or shutting-down, are not included, but the production during stable operation conditions. Storage and transportation of the final product are also not included. It is assumed that the manufacturing plants are located in an urban/industrial area and consequently the emissions are categorised as emanating in a high population density area. The emissions into water are assumed to be emitted into rivers.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From the reception of a mixture of boric oxide and carbon at the factory gate. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the production of boron carbide including materials, energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200125, '07ff3af2-1bf0-4ed5-862b-be000b0929af', 'market for bitumen seal, polymer EP4 flame retardant | bitumen seal, polymer EP4 flame retardant', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''bitumen seal, polymer EP4 flame retardant'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;The product "bitumen seal, polymer EP4 flame retardant" represents a bitumen sealing consisting of bitumen (major input in terms of mass), a fleece layer (glass fibre, polyester, glass etc.), limestone and schist meal, as well as sand and talcum. The product is applicable in the construction building sector. Bitumen sealing is used to protect the construction against water intrusion, mainly in flat roofed houses and in road construction work. The bitumen sealing types described in ecoinvent are V60, Alu80, VA4 and EP4 flam. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''bitumen seal, polymer EP4 flame retardant'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''bitumen seal, polymer EP4 flame retardant'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200126, '07ff5f2b-aa2c-4199-8adf-030158ab1c39', 'market for residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste polyurethane | residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste polyurethane', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste polyurethane'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200127, '08041756-73c7-494b-a02b-5a384840f350', 'market for bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste paperboard | bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste paperboard', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste paperboard'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200128, '0806627a-bd73-45c8-91ac-728b566bbf4a', 'market for bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF[W], waste plastic, consumer electronics | bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF[W], waste plastic, consumer electronics', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF[W], waste plastic, consumer electronics'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200129, '082c10a5-6a97-45c3-b442-d9016761a84f', 'market for steel removed by milling, small parts | steel removed by milling, small parts', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''steel removed by milling, small parts'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''steel removed by milling, small parts''. Milling is a chipping process where the piece of the material is fixed to a movable table while the cutting energy is provided by the rotating cutting tool. It is used for complex shaping and it can be applied to metals, wood and plastic materials. This dataset represents the milling of 1kg of steel in small parts. The service includes materials input, production infrastructure, energy consumption, water consumption and materials end-of-life. Degreasing is not included and has to be added if necessary. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200130, '0840bd2e-ab21-4470-b854-7044bc7f8fb8', 'market for computer, laptop | computer, laptop', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''computer, laptop'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the product of a laptop computer. Its production represents a typical laptop computer in the last 3 years before the reference year 2005 (Pentium 3) with a processor speed 600 MHz, 10 GB RAM, 128 MB memory, 12.1 inch screen, and a total mass with expansion base 3.15 kg. The expansion base is included without speaker, switch and cables. Its production represents all materials necessary to construct it and energy consumption during manufacturing. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''computer, laptop'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''computer, laptop'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200131, '08706584-4224-4c05-900c-ad29872b7278', 'market for gas power plant, 300MW electrical | gas power plant, 300MW electrical', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''gas power plant, 300MW electrical'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a gas power plant, 300MW electrical. The infrastructure represents an average gas power plant with a 300 MWe capacity and an assumed lifetime for operation of 180,000 h (approximately 5,000 h/a, 36 years of operation). Gas power plants can be used to cover peak loads. As a result, the annual number of operating hours can be relatively low. The process includes all materials necessary to construct it and energy consumption during manufacturing. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200132, '0888c962-2b48-460a-922e-6ac6fdbf8774', 'market for deinked pulp, wet lap | deinked pulp, wet lap', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''deinked pulp, wet lap'', in the Global geography. This is a constrained market for consequential system model, for attributional system models, this is a regular market. In the case of consequential system model, details about the marginal consumer can be found in the comment of the conditional exchange (by-product).;No transport or losses are considered in the modelling of this market, as producers and consumers are not physically separated.;The product “deinked pulp, wet lap” is a type of bleached, recycled pulp made from wastepaper fibres. Production includes a deinking process, i.e. the removal pf ink from the wastepaper input. In the ecoinvent database, deinked pulp is used for the production of wood free paper. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''deinked pulp, wet lap'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of deinked pulp, wet lap'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200133, '088c5d7e-9a8c-429c-80bb-b494449aac3f', 'transport, passenger aircraft, all distances to generic market for transport, passenger aircraft, unspecified | transport, passenger aircraft, unspecified', 'This is a linking activity which transfers part of the production volume of the specific transport, passenger, aircraft of all distances to the generic market for transport, passenger, aircraft, unspecified.;The transport, passenger, lorry, unspecified is meant to be used by activities, where the distance of the transport supplied is unkown. The activity starts with the input of the transport activities for the different flight distances. The mix is based on the production volumes of the respective transforming activities. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the supply of 1 person*km of generic (i.e. unspecified) transport.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200134, '088e24f0-871b-402a-8b57-2859d2237d29', 'treatment of residue from shredder fraction from manual dismantling, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of ''residue from shredder fraction from manual dismantling'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: Only for incineration of shredder residues generated in the recycling (manual dismantling) of electronic wasteInventoried waste contains several fractions: 1.6% rubber; 39.3% Plastics from electronic consumer goods; 39.3% Plastics from electronic industrial goods; 2.96% MSWI iron scrap; 5.92% Alu in MSW; 7.02% Glass; 3.54% wiring copper; 0.34% Pb in ASR inert; 0.0393% silver; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 28.98 MJ/kg; net heating value 27.77 MJ/kg; H2O 8610.5; O 77960; H 59861; C 653710; S 356.87; N 10451; P 416.59; B na; Cl 5632.3; Br 4325.2; F 196.45; I na; Ag 393.23; As 5.8936; Ba 139.09; Cd 118.66; Co 23.164; Cr 98.091; Cu 38276; Hg 0.66795; Mn 76.478; Mo 2.3574; Ni 425.1; Pb 3530.6; Sb 3774.3; Se 1.5398; Sn 179.36; V 7.991; Zn 610.71; Be 0.36663; Sc na; Sr 64.894; Ti 3518.1; Tl 0.2933; W na; Si 28447; Fe 25379; Ca 7555.7; Al 61109; K 91.94; Mg na; Na 4634.1. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 95.26%; Alu: 96.96%; Copper: 93.07%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 14.001g iron scrap, 18.267g aluminium scrap, 10.963g copper scrap. Net energy production: 3.52MJ/kg electric energy and 6.9MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200135, '0896e9e0-056e-450e-86a5-cfc6bf616c30', 'market for sawdust, loose, wet, measured as dry mass | sawdust, loose, wet, measured as dry mass', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sawdust, loose, wet, measured as dry mass'', in the Global geography.;It is considered that saw dust, loose is an intermediate product, that is always treated in the same place where it is produced, the sawing mill, normally by suction, so no transport is added to this market.;Sawdust is a by-product from the sawing process of sawlog and veneer log in the sawmill. The amount is expressed as dry mass. Loose sawdust is further transported via aspiration (suction) and collected at a silo at the sawmill site. With the production of saw dust, loose in the sawing mill. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. With the saw dust, loose taken care within the same facility.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200136, '089b4cba-803c-461a-af9d-44703089ae4f', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI, waste cement-fibre slab, dismantled, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI, waste cement-fibre slab, dismantled', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in slag compartment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Bottom ash is the by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''waste cement-fibre slab, dismantled''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste cement-fibre slab, dismantled''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 100%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200137, '08a75a58-a76a-4661-88c6-e3edbbdd7e8a', 'treatment of used industrial electronic device, mechanical treatment | used industrial electronic device', 'The process represents the treatment ''used industrial electronic device'' by mechanical dismantling in various fractions. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends when the used industrial electronic device has been dismantled mechanically.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200138, '08a8eccf-8a21-4080-b791-544d5e05cfb0', 'treatment of used intermodal shipping container, 45-foot, high-cube | used intermodal shipping container, 45-foot, high-cube', 'This dataset represents the treatment of used intermodal shipping container. The activity starts when the used container enters the waste treatment facility. The data on energy needed during dismantling are unknown. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends by different waste materials being ready for further treatment.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200139, '08d96612-fd3d-48ab-b7b4-717f6039b4ae', 'market for wastewater from textile production | wastewater from textile production', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is a market dataset for wastewater from the textile industry. It connects the producting activity of this wastewater with the datasets treating it. Therefore, there is no transportation considered in this market. Starts with the supply of wastewater from the datasets producing it. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Ends with the provision of the wastewater from the textile industry to its treatment/disposal consumption mix.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200140, '08e824ad-401c-4f50-9018-52269a6ace2d', 'stearic acid production | glycerine', 'This activity represents the production of 1kg of stearic acid. Stearic acid is a fatty acid with C18. Fatty acids are present in nature in fats and oils. Stearic acid is present in a weight concertation between 1 to 7 % in common vegetable oils (cotton seed, peanut, coconut, linseed, palm kernel, olive, rape-seed, castor, soybean, sunflower and palm). Stearic acid is found in very high concentration, 15 to 30% in beef tallow (Anneken et al. 2006).;Anneken et al. (2006) lists the following industries as the main application of fatty acids: soaps; detergents; cosmetics; textile; coatings and inks; rubber and tyres; candles and waxes; plastics; paper and leather; lubricants; emulsifiers; food (Anneken et al. 2006).;Fatty acids from tallow are mainly used in all the above-mentioned industries apart from coatings and inks and it is less prominent in the candles and waxes making (Anneken et al. 2006).;Reference(s): ;Anneken et al. (2006) Fatty Acids. Ullmann''s Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry. Volume 14, pp. 73-116. Wiley-VCH, Weinheim. The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Materials entering the process are included as well as energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200141, '08f2919d-2854-4320-9cdc-101af0534bc1', 'silicon tetrachloride production | silicon tetrachloride', 'Production of silicon tetrachloride production by chlorination method using silica sand as raw material. The activity starts when the raw materials enters the process. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Materials entering the process are included as well as energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200142, '0926e7a8-b704-41a0-bba5-08c91f13a58c', 'market for waste paper, sorted | waste paper, sorted', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''waste paper, sorted'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200143, '092da898-71c5-425c-a66a-a66f71a6eb68', 'market for peat moss | peat moss', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''peat moss'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;peat moss'' is an organic substance. Its used in medicine, personal care, food industry and as a fuel. If used as a fuel, it has a combustion value of 17.88 MJ/kg and is used as a domestic and seldom industrial power source. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''peat moss'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''peat moss'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200144, '09379415-e81a-4a64-951e-0c2100960894', 'machine construction, for treatment of waste electric and electronic equipment | machine, for treatment of waste electric and electronic equipment', 'The data represent an example of a mechanical treatment line for WEEE – comprising an initial shredder, a magnetic separator and an Eddy-current separator, a second (smaller) shredder, followed again by a magnetic separator and an Eddy-current separator – all this linked by conveyor belts. Total weight data are taken from producer information of such machines and own assumptions. Composition, infrastructure and production efforts are based on own assumptions. The dataset represents a production line with a total weight of 35’000 kg.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This module includes material, production efforts (transportation, energy, …) and the infrastructure for the production of all the machineries used for the mechanical treatment of WEEE devices. No information about emissions (air, water) and waste are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200145, '0999fb8b-5efa-4683-b729-ff67d42f53e7', 'market for antimony slag, water-quenched | antimony slag, water-quenched', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''antimony slag, water-quenched'''' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200146, '099bbba3-dc8f-43ea-b0d5-a52c38072fb8', 'market for expanded clay | expanded clay', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''expanded clay'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;The product "expanded clay" represents clay expanded by heat. Its production includes mined clay being mixed with water, ground, sometimes granulated and burned at reverse flow in a rotary furnace at 1’200 °C. The included organic materials burn and the clay pellets expand with the help of heavy fuel oil. The surface melts and produces a sintered shell. Expanded at 1’200 °C in a rotary furnace. Heavy fuel oil is used for heating. Bulk density of expanded clay: 260 - 500kg/m3. Expanded clay is mainly used as a lightweight aggregate for lightweight concrete blocks and thermal plaster. It is also used as sound and thermal bulk insulation. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''expanded clay'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''expanded clay'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200147, '099f85ae-b0ad-48a6-b954-6ec44fd77961', 'dryer production | dryer', 'This activity represents the production and disposal of an average domestic dryer. The appliance is 50 kg in mass and has the envisaged lifetime of 12.5 years. It is manufactured in Europe.The figures on material inputs from technosphere and energy required to produce an average dryer are taken from Fulvio and Peiro 2015. The figure on the annual production volume is assumed to be equal to the annual world sales and is extrapolated from Euromonitor International 2011 and ETSAP 2012. This activity starts with the reception of materials at the factory. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity includes the processes of material and energy use in manufacturing of an average dryer. The inventory additionally accounts for disposal of all materials. Packaging is not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200148, '09b39861-56bd-4b32-8c49-df3552c1e650', 'market for motor scooter, 50 cubic cm engine | motor scooter, 50 cubic cm engine', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''motor scooter, 50 cubic cm engine'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This product is a mobile infrastructure that is used in the service of transportation. The vehicle operates with petrol, it runs with 60-70km/h at max. speed and its operation emissions represents average values for Swiss 50cc-150cc fleet. Its occupation is to carry 1.1 person and it has a lifetime expectancy of 50,000km. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''motor scooter, 50 cubic cm engine'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''motor scooter, 50 cubic cm engine'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200149, '09c37a27-ef28-4847-a3b3-36d54fb021d3', 'market for sweet gas, burned in gas turbine | sweet gas, burned in gas turbine', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sweet gas, burned in gas turbine'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;''sweet gas, burned in gas turbine'' describes the use of a fossil fuel. It is used as a gaseous fuel and is sourced from natural gas processing plants. This exchange provides the treatment of sweet gas (hydrogen sulfide poor) to produce electricity. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''sweet gas, burned in gas turbine'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of sweet gas, burned in gas turbine'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200150, '09d4d8d5-25f4-4648-8420-d49f1598b861', 'treatment of residue from shredder fraction from manual dismantling, municipal incineration | electricity, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of ''residue from shredder fraction from manual dismantling'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: Only for incineration of shredder residues generated in the recycling (manual dismantling) of electronic wasteInventoried waste contains several fractions: 1.6% rubber; 39.3% Plastics from electronic consumer goods; 39.3% Plastics from electronic industrial goods; 2.96% MSWI iron scrap; 5.92% Alu in MSW; 7.02% Glass; 3.54% wiring copper; 0.34% Pb in ASR inert; 0.0393% silver; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 28.98 MJ/kg; net heating value 27.77 MJ/kg; H2O 8610.5; O 77960; H 59861; C 653710; S 356.87; N 10451; P 416.59; B na; Cl 5632.3; Br 4325.2; F 196.45; I na; Ag 393.23; As 5.8936; Ba 139.09; Cd 118.66; Co 23.164; Cr 98.091; Cu 38276; Hg 0.66795; Mn 76.478; Mo 2.3574; Ni 425.1; Pb 3530.6; Sb 3774.3; Se 1.5398; Sn 179.36; V 7.991; Zn 610.71; Be 0.36663; Sc na; Sr 64.894; Ti 3518.1; Tl 0.2933; W na; Si 28447; Fe 25379; Ca 7555.7; Al 61109; K 91.94; Mg na; Na 4634.1. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 95.26%; Alu: 96.96%; Copper: 93.07%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 14.001g iron scrap, 18.267g aluminium scrap, 10.963g copper scrap. Net energy production: 3.52MJ/kg electric energy and 6.9MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200151, '09ded00e-d36c-40c9-9334-e4269dc7f9cf', 'market for transport, freight, lorry with refrigeration machine, 3.5-7.5 ton, EURO6, carbon dioxide, liquid refr(...)_13 | transport, freight, lorry with refrigeration machine, 3.5-7.5 ton, EURO6, carbon dioxide, liquid refrigerant, freezing', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''transport, freight, lorry with refrigeration machine, 3.5-7.5 ton, EURO6, carbon dioxide, liquid refrigerant, freezing'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of transportation of 1 metric ton across the distance of 1 km. This service only considers the transportation of refrigerated goods. The vehicle operates with diesel and uses carbon dioxide as a refrigerant, its emission standard is classified as EURO6 and it has a lorry size class of 3.5-7.5 metric tons. It is an average lorry in the referring weight class (net weight 6800t). It has a life span of 15 years and a lifetime capacity of 540,000 km Data for transport is calculated for an average load factor, including empty return trips. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200152, '09e2e15e-0f3f-4af0-b3a4-216d584918fc', 'market for slaughterhouse waste | slaughterhouse waste', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''slaughterhouse waste'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200153, '09e92a17-b39b-4b72-b57f-c8c1fa22116d', 'market for mint | mint', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''mint'', in the Global geography.;In this market, default transport model and expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The default transport distances are built on a generic model which assigns the transport distances based on the ISIC code. This approach is, especially in case of fruits and vegetables, rather coarse. So in a certain cases expert judgement is used to adjust the default distances.;;The transport distances and associated impacts presented in the markets represents the average scenario for given geography. In case of fruits and vegetables the final impact at the consumer vary a lot depending on whether the food is consumed near the producer or far. The average impact of, for example, banana is overestimated if the consumer is present in Brazil and it is heavily underestimated is the consumer is present in Europe. The markets are modelled so, that editing to model concrete scenario is possible and easy.;;Fruits and vegetables are traded all over the world on an increasing scale. ;It is assumed, that all mint which are transported are being transported by infrastructure equipped for transport of goods in need of atmosphere control.;;The recomended conditions for transport of mint are (Cantwell and Reid 2001);;;temperature: 0 to +5 °C;humidity (relative): 95 %;approximate shelf life (in ambient air): 2 to 3 weeks;;Cantwell and Reid, 2001, Herbs (Fresh Culinary): Recommendations for Maintaining Postharvest Quality. Retrieved from: http://postharvest.ucdavis.edu/pfvegetable/Herbs/, accessed 25th May 2016;;The product ''mint'' is a spice/aromatic crop. It is a perennial crop. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''mint'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''mint'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are considered.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200154, '09ed289d-efd8-41a2-890c-bfd93214fb72', 'market for feldspar | feldspar', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''feldspar'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;The product "feldspar" represents a group of minerals (CaAl2SiO8). Feldspar is a raw material for glass, ceramics, fillers, and enamel frits and glazes. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''feldspar'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''feldspar'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200155, '0a0c7277-99b1-4441-8c1a-6688fe477c0c', 'market for dolomite quarry infrastructure | dolomite quarry infrastructure', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''dolomite quarry infrastructure'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a dolomite quarry infrastructure. The mine has a yearly yield of about 380,000 tons and a lifetime of 50 years. The process includes the land-use of the built part of the mine, the production places and the paved roads. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200156, '0a34294b-b730-4f81-982e-406455512be7', 'market for sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, WW from maize starch production | sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, WW from maize starch production', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, WW from maize starch production'', in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200157, '0a363ede-bf08-4546-9cfa-050291b78909', 'market for furnace, pellet, 15kW | furnace, pellet, 15kW', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''furnace, pellet, 15kW'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the product of a pellet furnace. It has a lifetime of 20 years for the furnace and the automatic control system, 80 years for the chimney, while its operation time is 2,100 h/year and capacity of 15 kW. This is used as a central heating system for a single-family house. The process includes the most important materials used for the fabrication of the furnace, the water storage and the chimney, their end-of-life, storage area and energy used for the construction. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''furnace, pellet, 15kW'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''furnace, pellet, 15kW'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200158, '0a3850b9-9869-426a-9ff8-d58f32eb04a5', 'market for finishing, textile, knit cotton | finishing, textile, knit cotton', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''finishing, textile, knit cotton'', in the Global geography.;This market is not considering transportation since the service is produced and consumed in physically the same location.;This is delivering the service of ''finishing, textile, knit cotton'' and includes all necessary materials, energy, water, waste, wastewater (produced within the process) and infrastructure in order to process 1 kg of cotton textile that is produced through knitting. Finishing is a process applied after dying and aims at improving the appearance and texture of the textile. A user should use this service alongside 1.01 kg of textile, knit cotton. Activity starts with the production of the service of finishing, textile, knit cotton. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Activity ends with the provision of the service of finishing, textile, knit cotton.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200159, '0a4be8d1-e1d6-4700-b2fb-10acb4ba1f14', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 97% water, WWT-SLF[W], waste plastic, consumer electronics, landfarming | sewage sludge, 97% water, WWT-SLF[W], waste plastic, consumer electronics', 'The process represents the treatment of landfarming of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Sewage sludge with 97% water is generated during wastewater treatement (WWT) of leachate from the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of ''waste plastic, consumer electronics'' . Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste plastic, consumer electronics'' having wet (W) infiltration class. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available for landfarming. Collection and transportation of the waste to this process is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfarming process are released to the environment (air, water and soil). The activity is considering local fate of emissions and the initial specific wastewater composition (generating the sewage sludge). Further, it includes provision of fertiliser functions for N, P, K, if present in the sludge.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200160, '0a5db842-bd7c-41b7-9042-215b4a450ed7', 'market for potassium nitrate, agricultural grade | potassium nitrate, agricultural grade', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This activity represents the market for 1 kg of potassium nitrate, agricultural grade. Agricultural grade potassium nitrate has a purity of around 50%.;Transport distances are taken from the ecoinvent Global default transport model, available on the ecoinvent website www.ecoinvent.org. Activity starts with the product ready for transport. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Activity ends with the delivery of the product to the consumer.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200161, '0a6ee4ee-f591-40cf-a0a6-16528a9b7858', 'market for expansion vessel, 80l | expansion vessel, 80l', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''expansion vessel, 80l'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the product of an expansion vessel with a capacity of 80 liters that is used for heat exchange fluid used in a solar collector system. In order to accommodate the thermal expansion of the heat exchange fluid, an expansion vessel is required. The vessel should be designed in such a way that, in addition to the expansion that normally occurs in operation, the entire contents of the collector field can also be absorbed. A lifetime of 25 years is assumed for the whole solar collector system. The process includes all materials necessary to construct it, energy consumption during manufacturing and decommission but excludes infrastructure. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200162, '0a758d26-88e2-4128-bbd2-3dc00acfc6e0', 'market for aluminium removed by drilling, conventional | aluminium removed by drilling, conventional', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''aluminium removed by drilling, conventional'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''aluminium removed by drilling, conventional''. Drilling uses a rotating cutting tool (the drill bit) to remove material from the work piece and it predominately uses the front end for cutting. It is applied for shapes like circular cavity or holes. The process is conventional, meaning that it is controlled manually and needs constant supervision. This dataset represents the drilling of 1 kg of aluminium. The service includes materials input, production infrastructure, machinery and electricity consumption. Maintenance and tool (bit) replacements are not included. Degreasing is not included and has to be added if necessary. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200163, '0a7f2d8e-505d-4368-972f-1a49e7b19c98', 'market for zinc oxide | zinc oxide', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''zinc oxide'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''zinc oxide'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''zinc oxide'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200164, '0a92716e-aa4c-4caf-9afe-cd677b215f89', 'market for electricity, high voltage, cobalt industry | electricity, high voltage, cobalt industry', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of high voltage electricity to the cobalt industry. The data were copied from the global (GLO) dataset "market for electricity, high voltage, cobalt industry". This activity starts from 1kWh of electricity fed into the high voltage transmission network. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the transport of 1 kWh of high voltage electricity in the transmission network over aerial lines and cables. This dataset includes: - electricity inputs produced in this country and from imports - the transmission network - direct emissions to air (ozone and N2O). - electricity losses during transmission This dataset doesn''t include - electricity losses during transformation, as these are included in the dataset for transformation - Zinc emissions from steel masts. Steel masts used for aerial lines are coated in order to prevent corrosion. The commonly used process is hot-dip galvanising using zinc as anticorrosive. In general a duplex process is used applying a zinc and paint coating to further improve the corrosion protection. In addition, the selection of the colour can improve the embedding into the landscape <van Oeteren 1988>. With this additional protection the zinc emissions into soil can be neglected <van Oeteren 1988>. - leakage of insulation oil from cables and electro technical equipment (transformers, switchgear, circuit breakers) because this only happens in case of accidental release - data for electromagnetic fields - SF6 emissions during the transmission, as these are allocated to the market dataset for medium voltage. - SF6 emissions during production and deconstruction of the switchgear, as these are accounted for in the transmission network dataset. K.-A. van Oeteren, ''Feuerverzinkung'', expert-Verlag, Ehningen 1988', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200165, '0a9d59dc-ee54-4787-ae96-fd2c0a448aa8', 'nutrient supply from ash, from combustion of straw | organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N', 'This inventory describes the application of ash, from combustion of straw. This application provides the nutrients of N and P2O5 contained in the ash. No emissions are considered. Activity starting with the application ash from combustion of straw. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the provision of N-fertiliser and P-fertiliser.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200166, '0ab12f5d-fd78-4645-b5b1-4393d32e7791', 'market for nuclear waste storage, interim, for high level radioactive waste before final repository | nuclear waste storage, interim, for high level radioactive waste before final repository', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''nuclear waste storage, interim, for high level radioactive waste before final repository'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a nuclear waste storage, interim, for high level radioactive waste before final repository. The infrastructure has a capacity for approximately 20,000 m3 of conditioned waste. The interim nuclear waste storage uses an area of approximately 32''000 m2 industrial area. Half of this area (16''000 m2) is accounted for in this module and the other half is accounted for in the module "nuclear waste storage, interim, for low level radioactive waste before final repository". The construction time of the facility is 5 years and the operating time is 55 years. The process includes building materials, energy consumption during construction and decommiddioning (electricity and diesel oil), land use and decommission from dismantling of the buildings. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200167, '0ad32b7b-f176-417f-9434-385b2367b7af', 'market for diesel-electric generating set, 10MW | diesel-electric generating set, 10MW', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''diesel-electric generating set, 10MW'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;Thisis an immobile infrastructure, representing the product of an diesel-electric generating set. The infrasrtucture has a capacity of 10MW. It is used for generating electricity for oil and natural gas exploration and production. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200168, '0ad3606e-d70a-4412-b6e5-4a987f215212', 'gadolinium oxide to generic market for mischmetal | mischmetal', 'This is a renaming activity. It''s purpose is to link ''europium oxide'' to the generic ''market for mischmetal''. Activity starts with the reception of ''europium oxide''. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Activity ends with the ''mischmetal'' being ready for transportation.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200169, '0ae69502-f74b-4c59-bb14-90b6ead21f9e', 'market for impact extrusion of steel, cold, 5 strokes | impact extrusion of steel, cold, 5 strokes', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''impact extrusion of steel, cold, 5 strokes'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is delivering the service of ''impact extrusion of steel, cold, 5 strokes''. Impact extrusion is a manufacturing process that the product is made out of metal slug. It is a type of pressure forming that take advantage of the change in hardness of materials under high pressure. A pressure force of typically 3.2 to 10 MN is applied which leads to yielding of the materials and a forming of the slug according to the mould`s shape. The use of multiple strokes it is possible to produce complex shapes. Cold impact extrusion is performed in room temperature. This dataset represents cold impact extrusion of 1 kg of steel with 5 stroke. The service includes impact extrusion processes, production infrastructure, machinery but it excludes the steel input and the process of degreasing. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200170, '0af693e4-899a-4fed-a76d-e74b661394d9', 'nutrient supply from manure, solid, cattle | organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5', 'This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''manure, solid, cattle'''' for fertiliser use.;No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use. The purpose of this activity is to connect the chemical production of ''''manure, solid, cattle'''' with its generic uses as fertilizer. The product ''''manure, solid, cattle'''' is connected to the generic market for ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' through this supplying activity. In the agricultural context, ''''manure, solid, cattle'''' can be used directly as a fertilizer input to crop production, eventually with other chemicals; alternatively, a generic input of ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' can be used instead, and this will represent the regional consumption mix for his type of nutrient. A way in between is allowed by using the generic input ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' and link to the activity providing it from a specific chemical.;In all cases, emissions associated to the application of the fertilizer have to be calculated in the crop production activity. This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''manure, solid, cattle'''' for fertiliser use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200171, '0afd3f42-8f48-44ae-9182-4d0fa2c92f49', 'market for waste reinforced plasterboard | waste reinforced plasterboard', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''waste reinforced plasterboard'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200172, '0b097b9e-8a80-4cc4-8850-4e9a9633c19e', 'market for transport, passenger car, small size, petrol, EURO 4 | transport, passenger car, small size, petrol, EURO 4', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''transport, passenger car, small size, petrol, EURO 4'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of average transportation of passenger/s across one kilometre (km). This service only considers the transportation of passengers. The vehicle operates with petrol, its emission standard is classified as EURO4. The average passenger load factor is considered to in total 97.2 kg. The dry weight of the vehicle is considered to be 1200 kg and its lifetime is 150000 km. A user that wish to model a different average load factor should modify this product or its producing activity. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200173, '0b3615e6-5182-4d7d-aabe-722a83cfbcba', 'market for power block, solar thermal parabolic trough, 50 MW | power block, solar thermal parabolic trough, 50 MW', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''power block, solar thermal parabolic trough, 50 MW'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a power block, solar thermal parabolic trough, 50 MW. The infrastructure manily consists of pressure vessels, compressors, heat exchangers with cooling towers and steam turbine generators. It has a capacity of 50 MW and a lifetime of 30 years. The process includes building materials and their decommission, energy and water consumption during production. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200174, '0b3dda75-e440-46ad-a7b5-7708d10f05a2', 'market for photovoltaic slanted-roof installation, 3kWp, multi-Si, panel, mounted, on roof | photovoltaic slanted-roof installation, 3kWp, multi-Si, panel, mounted, on roof', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''photovoltaic slanted-roof installation, 3kWp, multi-Si, panel, mounted, on roof'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the installation of a photovoltaic slanted-roof, 3kWp, multi-Si, panel, mounted, on roof. The infrastructure has a capacity of 3kWp and a lifetime of 30 years. The process includes all the components for the installation of a photovoltaic plant, energy use for the mounting, and decommission. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200175, '0b4b495b-9065-4d71-b4c1-f6f7857d1670', 'market for chlorothalonil | chlorothalonil', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''chlorothalonil'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;chlorothalonil'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 001897-45-6. It is called ''2,4,5,6-tetrachlorobenzene-1,3-dicarbonitrile'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C8Cl4N2. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure and appears as colourless crystals with no distinct odour. It is nearly insoluble in water, but fairly soluble in benzene, xylene and acetone. It is modelled as a pure substance. On a consumer level, is used in the following products: fungicides. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''chlorothalonil'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''chlorothalonil'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200176, '0b50d6da-74ba-4162-b8cc-24f49b5d4e31', 'market for cobalt carbonate | cobalt carbonate', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the global market for cobalt carbonate. It includes estimates for average transport requirements from producing to using entity This dataset starts with cobalt carbonate leaving the gate of the producing entity, ready for distribution to using entities. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the supply of cobalt carbonate to the activities that consume it.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200177, '0b67d8eb-f6f2-4eb2-a631-39da0ca4a100', 'market for furrowing, sugarcane | furrowing, sugarcane', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''furrowing, sugarcane'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''furrowing, sugarcane'' on an area of one hectare. It includes the use of diesel powered mobile infrastructure (tractors, machinery). Diesel combustion linearly affects direct emissions. Hence, a user can model the right amount of this service by using information on diesel consumption. For example: If within the user''s model diesel consumption is 30 kg/ha while in this service it is 15 kg/ha, the user can model with 2 ha of this service. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200178, '0b778e96-ae53-46aa-8829-07c9e3d02d6b', 'treatment of waste plastic, consumer electronics, open burning | waste plastic, consumer electronics', 'This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of ''waste plastic, consumer electronics'' in uncontrolled, open burning. Recommended use of this dataset: uncontrolled disposal of the waste through burning. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% plastics from electronic consumer goods. Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 36.29 MJ/kg; net heating value 34.78 MJ/kg; H2O 11129; O 41000; H 75000; C 821000; S 300; N 13100; P 600; B na; Cl 6300; Br 6800; F 130; I na; Ag na; As 10; Ba 137; Cd 115; Co 29.478; Cr 34; Cu 3194.1; Hg 1.4; Mn 4; Mo 2; Ni 703; Pb 127; Sb 4795.2; Se 1.9596; Sn 267; V 0.5; Zn 361; Be 0.46656; Sc na; Sr 82.582; Ti 4187; Tl 0.37325; W na; Si 3547; Fe 1483; Ca 3177; Al 2020; K 233; Mg na; Na 128. Share of carbon in waste that is biogenic 0%. Recycling rates for metallic iron = 0% for metallic aluminium = 0% for metallic copper = 0% . A mass of 0.061 kg residues are left on ground. The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the uncontrolled disposal location is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open burning are released to the environment (air and soil).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200179, '0ba33f78-77e4-4d06-a9db-bef8273e55ab', 'transport, freight, lorry with refrigeration machine, 7.5-16 ton, EURO6, R134a refrigerant, cooling | transport, freight, lorry with refrigeration machine, 7.5-16 ton, EURO6, R134a refrigerant, cooling', 'This dataset represents transport of goods in lorry with atmosphere controlled (temperature, humidity, etc.) storage space set up for cooling.;While the majority of the atmosphere controlled (cold chain, refrigerated transport) road transportation is conducted with truck with semi-trailer in the cities this goods is often transported by smaller rigid trucks with refrigeration machine. This activity starts with input of fuel, road and vehicle infrastructure including refrigeration machine. It includes also exhaust and non-exhaust emissions. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This datasets combines the transport of 1 ton of goods over 1km by a lorry with refrigeration machine. The goods themselves are not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200180, '0ba40e88-e0ca-4bb0-bd57-314780f3c383', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste polyurethane, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, waste polyurethane', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in slag compartment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Bottom ash is the by-product of municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of sewage sludge (with 70% water) that in turn is generated during wastewater treatment (WWT) of leachate from the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of ''waste polyurethane''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste polyurethane''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200181, '0bab8f7f-3e65-4a20-baf8-d0f2d3fcc5d7', 'market for photovoltaic flat-roof installation, 3kWp, single-Si, on roof | photovoltaic flat-roof installation, 3kWp, single-Si, on roof', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''photovoltaic flat-roof installation, 3kWp, single-Si, on roof'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the installation of a photovoltaic flat-roof, 3kWp, multi-Si, on roof. It has a capacity of 3kWp and a lifetime of 30 years. The process includes all the components for the installation of a photovoltaic plant, energy use for the mounting and decommission. The installation of modules on flat roofs is a quite common type of installation. They are used for small plants on dwellings (3 kWp). This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200182, '0bcb8881-9742-4878-8171-946a4e1ee0a6', 'lime, from liquid packaging board production to generic market for soil pH raising agent | soil pH raising agent, as CaCO3', 'This is a renaming activity. Its purpose is to link ''lime, from liquid packaging board production'' to the ''generic market for soil pH raising agent''. All products that enter this generic market provide the function of pH soil raising agent. Activity starts with the reception of ''lime, from liquid packaging board production''. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Activity ends with the ''soil pH raising agent, as CaCO3'' being ready for transportation.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200183, '0bd64369-fafc-45ae-a057-02d0b1a4bae8', 'wood preservative production, water-based, indoor use, dry | wood preservative, water-based, indoor use, dry', 'According to EN 335-1:2005, five use classes are distinguished for chemical wood protection based on the general exposure of wood in its application, wetting regime in service and the biological agents to be expected. This exposure scenario determines the potentially vulnerable zone of wood and the required treatment for the application of the wood preservative (see table) From reception of chemicals at the factory gate From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The datasets covers the components and preparation of a typical water-based/organic solvent based [as applicable] wood preservative for the use class according to EN 335-1:2006 as indicated in the name of the dataset, ready to be packed. In addition in contains an estimate for electricity consumption and for infrastructure. Packaging is not included', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200184, '0bd652af-2d1e-4a25-a1f8-b3f9884a9bc9', 'offshore well production, oil/gas | offshore well, oil/gas', 'This activity represents all types of offshore drilling operations for the production of crude petroleum oil and natural gas.;;Following the approach of Meili et al. (2021), the emissions due to venting and flaring are excluded from this inventory as they are covered with the new data for the overall venting and flaring in crude oil and natural gas extraction. (as described in chapter 9.2 of Meili et al., 2021). Also, the energy use for well drilling is covered in the general data on energy consumption and not recorded separately for this activity.;Source: C. Meili, N. Jungbluth, M. Bussa (2021) Life cycle inventories of crude oil and natural gas extraction. ESU-services Ltd. commissioned by the Federal Office for the Environment (FOEN) and the “Verband der Schweizerischen Gasindustrie (VSG), Schaffhausen, Switzerland, DOI: 10.13140/RG.2.2.29142.78409, http://esu-services.ch/data/public-lci-reports/ From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. All energy uses, materials and emissions for drilling of an offshore bore hole and finishing of the well.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200185, '0c0710fa-6f90-49d9-af52-ccf97d4f9331', 'market for bottom ash, MSWI, waste plastic, mixture | bottom ash, MSWI, waste plastic, mixture', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''bottom ash, MSWI, waste plastic, mixture'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200186, '0c099fa2-7b89-4e96-aefc-3cf85d5cdcb9', 'market for deep drawing, steel, 3500 kN press, single stroke | deep drawing, steel, 3500 kN press, single stroke', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''deep drawing, steel, 3500 kN press, single stroke'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is delivering the service of ''deep drawing, steel, 3500 kN press, single stroke''. Deep drawing in the technology of stretching a sheet metal (called blank) into a hollow shape. A punch presses the blank through the die cavity that defines the shape. The service represents the deep drawing of steel with 3500 kN press in single stroke mode and includes energy consumption, production infrastructure and machinery, but it excludes the steel input. Degreasing is also not included, so it has to be added if necessary. Deep drawing steel is used when complex geometries with straight sides are required in the end product, like automotive industry. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200187, '0c3a1453-8bcf-4cbd-a2fb-08189306fdd3', 'market for electronics, for control units | electronics, for control units', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''electronics, for control units'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''electronics, for control units'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''electronics, for control units'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200188, '0c61d21f-6f56-40f1-9818-663efac67eb8', 'market for steel removed by turning, average, computer numerical controlled | steel removed by turning, average, computer numerical controlled', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''steel removed by turning, average, computer numerical controlled'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''steel removed by turning, average, computer numerical controlled''. Turning is a chipping process where the piece of material is rotating while the cutting tool is not. It can be applied to both inside and outside of the piece to be machined and it is normally used to produce cylindrical shapes. It is performed in metals, wood and plastic materials. The process is computer numerical controlled, meaning that it operates autonomously once programmed. This dataset represents the turning of 1 kg of steel. The service includes materials input, production infrastructure, machinery and electricity consumption. Degreasing is not included and has to be added if necessary. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200189, '0c79b3ed-c92d-4ed2-aa8f-78e8030f1d1e', 'treatment of waste refinery gas, burned in flare | waste refinery gas', 'Description of the direct emissions due to the combustion of refinery gas in refinery flares not including the infrastructure of the flare.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Combustion emissions.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200190, '0c89a6e7-f327-4fb1-8406-0395b1e09904', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 97% water, WWT-SLF[W], waste plastic, consumer electronics, landfarming | organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N', 'The process represents the treatment of landfarming of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Sewage sludge with 97% water is generated during wastewater treatement (WWT) of leachate from the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of ''waste plastic, consumer electronics'' . Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste plastic, consumer electronics'' having wet (W) infiltration class. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available for landfarming. Collection and transportation of the waste to this process is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfarming process are released to the environment (air, water and soil). The activity is considering local fate of emissions and the initial specific wastewater composition (generating the sewage sludge). Further, it includes provision of fertiliser functions for N, P, K, if present in the sludge.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200191, '0ca9f8da-c638-4792-a7af-df08de47f540', 'market for silver | silver', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''silver'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''silver'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''silver'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200192, '0cb416d9-2078-487d-a228-b2124226ce4b', 'blast furnace sludge, for recovery, Recycled Content cut-off | blast furnace sludge, for recovery', 'From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200193, '0cb8f263-da96-41f8-a0ab-f3254f59fbb8', 'mineral supplement production, for beef cattle | mineral supplement, for beef cattle', 'This dataset represents the production of mineral supplement, for beef cattle. The supplement is used to assist beef cattle production on pasture and complete the diet of the animals with micronutrients that are not usually present in the pasture. The nutrients and micronutrients are simply mixed. The dataset is constructed using literature and expert judgement. ;Literature: Composition of the proteic supplement is found online. Accessed on 25.06.2019 at: http://old.cnpgc.embrapa.br/publicacoes/naoseriadas/suplementacaomineral/ Activity starts with the reception of the necessary materials for the production of the mineral supplemnt. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Activity ends with the mineral supplement produced and being ready for transportation in the saline plant.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200194, '0cbe8763-09db-405c-a440-222323d5189e', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT, WW from CRT production, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively produced from another waste treatment. Municipal incineration is the controlled combustion of a waste. Sewage sludge is generated in the wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from CRT production''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from CRT production''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. "CRT" stands for "Cathode-ray tube". The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process are released to the environment (air and water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200195, '0cc5bd60-716d-4d57-9aac-fa5071bb7893', 'market for zirconium tetrachloride | zirconium tetrachloride', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''zirconium tetrachloride'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;Zirconium tetrachloride (Zirconium (IV) chloride – ZrCl4) is an inorganic compound which serves as an intermediate product for the production of other compounds of Zirconium. Its most prominent use is during the production of pure (nuclear and non-nuclear grade) zirconium metal through the Kroll process. Other applications include: i) usage as a weak Lewis acid for the Friedel-Crafts reaction, the Diels-Alder reaction and intra-molecular cyclisation reactions and be usage in water-repelent treatment of textiles and other fibrous materials. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''zirconium tetrachloride'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''zirconium tetrachloride'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200196, '0cd0bccd-ddeb-4d76-8950-8dd6a4d8cd5c', 'market for spent activated carbon with mercury | spent activated carbon with mercury', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''spent activated carbon with mercury'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200197, '0cf1e6b2-7852-40cd-993c-e136d1164bef', 'market for mercerizing, textile | mercerizing, textile', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of 1 kg of the service of ''mercerizing, fabric'' from activities that produce it within the geography of GLO. Transportation is excluded in this market. This activity starts at the site that ''mercerizing, fabric'' is offered as service within the geography of this dataset. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of 1 kg of ''mercerizing, fabric'' to the consumers of this product. Transport is not taken into account. No losses in service considered.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200198, '0d01ccdf-65ee-40a3-aab9-825de179d7a5', 'market for printed wiring board, through-hole mounted, unspecified, Pb free | printed wiring board, through-hole mounted, unspecified, Pb free', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''printed wiring board, through-hole mounted, unspecified, Pb free'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''printed wiring board, through-hole mounted, unspecified, Pb free'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''printed wiring board, through-hole mounted, unspecified, Pb free'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200199, '0d08b44b-b9ec-4d24-a206-6cc08d1f5c69', 'market for grass, organic | grass, organic', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''grass, organic'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The product ''grass, organic'' is a grain. It is an annual crop. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''grass, organic'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''grass, organic'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200200, '0d1fe735-9448-400a-adcd-07c06600abfe', 'marine electric motor construction | marine electric motor', 'This dataset represents the construction of electric motors and pumps used in marine applications, per 1000 kg of motor, based on an average electric motor composition. Provision of materials, construction of marine electric motors and pumps. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Metal works as proxy for the construction and assembly of all motor parts. End of life treatment. The Use phase of motors is modelled in the vessel''s Use phase.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200201, '0d216150-cc60-4bd9-a6be-0988282975a8', 'market for coffee maker | coffee maker', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''coffee maker'', in the Global geography.;Transport information are taken from the ecoinvent GLO transport model, excel accessible on the ecoinvent website "Default Transport Assumptions". Air transport is excluded based on expert judgement.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the product of a coffee maker that is used to produce coffe. It has a mass of 1.9 kg and a rating of 640 W, while its lifetime is estimated to be 5 years and its lifetime capacity 2129.16 hours. Its production represents all materials necessary to construct it, energy consumption during manufacturing and its end-of-life. The activity starts at factory gate with the final product ready for transport (packaging is not included). From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity includes the transport of the final good to the consumer.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200202, '0d22bfce-7465-4864-b0be-3e3cb77e6ba8', 'market for packaging, for pesticides | packaging, for pesticides', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset is a market dataset for packaging, for pesticides, which accounts for the delivery (transportation expenditures) of the packaging to the datsets consuming it.;The reference product refers to the amount of pesticide packed, not the amount of packaging material.;Default transportation values are used for plastic products from their production site to the site where they are filled with pesticides. Default transportation values are used for fertilisers from the site where the packaging is filled with pesticides till the farm that are finally used. The activity starts right after the production of the packaging, for pesticides. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the provision of the packaging, for pesticides, to its users.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200203, '0d2c75a8-30c0-4a5d-92b7-b192c0ed257b', 'bulk carrier production, for dry goods | bulk carrier, for dry goods', 'The dataset represents the manufacturing and disposal of one bulk carrier for dry goods with a load capacity (DWT) of 51,000 tonnes. End of life is not accounted for other than by the inclusion of materials disposed or recovered for recycling (energy and other requirements for ship dismantling are not included).;The material breakdown of a freight ship is from Jain et al., (2016), which together with the estimated lightweight mass of an average tanker, was used to calculate the tonnage of steel, copper, brass, zinc, machinery, electronics, insulation material, plastics and wood required for ship construction. ;The mass of paint used per lightweight tonne was determined from literature (Kameyama et al., n.d, Harish and Sunil, 2015, Nicolae et al., 2014). Emission of paint and volatiles (NMVOCs) are calculated applying emisison factors from OECD (2009). ;Estimates of electricity, fuels and other consumables (welding wire, carbon dioxide gas etc) required for construction were determined from LCA studies (Kameyama et al., n.d, Nicolae et al., 2014) and an energy efficiency study on shipbuilding (Harish and Sunil, 2015). Welding and cutting demand is estimated by back-calculating from the amount of welding gas consumed, as reported in Harish and Sunil (2015) .;The materials produced at ship end-of-life are included but no energy for dismantling the ship is included. ;The dataset does not include the chemicals, liquids and oils (e.g. lubricants, refigerants etc.) making up a portion of the ship''s weight. Outputs and emissions of liquid materials are thus also not included at end-of-life dismantling of the ship.;References: ;Jain, K., Pruyn, J. and Hopman, J. (2016) Quantitative assessment of material composition of end-of-life ships using onboard documentation, Resources, Conservation and Recycling, 107, pp. 1-9.;Harish, R. and Sunil, S. (2015) Energy Consumption and Conservation in Shipbuilding, International Journal of Innovative Research and Development, 4(7), pp. 26-31;Kameyama, M., Hiraoka, K. and Tauchi, H. (n.d) Study on Life Cycle Impact Assessment for Ships, Energy and Environment Department: Tokyo, Japan.;Nicolae, F., Popa, C. and Beizadae, H. (2014) Applications of Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) in Shipping Industry, 14th International Multidisciplinary Scientific GeoConference.;OECD (2009) OECD Series on Emission Scenario Documents Number 22: Emission Scenario Documents on Coating Industry, OECD: Paris, France Ship production, starting with receiving/obtaining the material inputs required for construction. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the production of one ship. The dataset includes material consumption (steel, copper, plastic, paint etc.), energy consumption (electricity and LPG), welding and cutting, and emissions of the solvent of painting as NMVOC. The dataset does not include the consumption of liquids and oils (e.g. lubricants, refigerants etc.) or energy required for dismantling the ship at end-of-life.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200204, '0d323230-946d-400b-9b74-7f6a57c5bbb8', 'market for dimethylamine borane | dimethylamine borane', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''dimethylamine borane'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;dimethylamine borane'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 000074-94-2. It is called ''dimethylamine borane'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C2H7BN. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure as a white solid. It is modelled as a pure substance. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: chemicals and pharmaceuticals. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''dimethylamine borane'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''dimethylamine borane'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200205, '0d4447dd-64a6-40d4-964a-5452afd3c80d', 'market for terbium oxide | terbium oxide', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''terbium oxide'', in the Global geography. This is a constrained market for consequential system model, for attributional system models, this is a regular market. In the case of consequential system model, details about the marginal consumer can be found in the comment of the conditional exchange (by-product).;This market represents the global supply of terbium oxide, which is produced exclusively as a by-product of rare earth oxide production;Transportation is included but no losses are assumed. The activity starts with the collection of terbium oxide from producers. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the transfer of terbium oxide to consumers.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200206, '0d56c9b1-5af0-4d17-b594-49188127526f', 'treatment of residues, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, laptop computer, residual material landfill | residues, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, laptop computer', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in residual material landfill of a waste (residues) that is exclusively produced in another waste treatment. Residues are a by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''residue from mechanical treatment, laptop computer''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''residue from mechanical treatment, laptop computer''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to river water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200207, '0d592912-a859-4f53-9678-7f52b48b425d', 'market for sodium chloroacetate | sodium chloroacetate', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of 1 kg of sodium chloroacetate from activities that produce it within the geography of this dataset.;The transport amounts are based on the default transport distances for markets, provided in the ''Default Transport Assumptions'' file available on the ecoinvent website (https://www.ecoinvent.org/support/documents-and-files/documents-and-files.html). See exchange comments for additional details. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce sodium chloroacetate within the geography of this dataset, with the product ready for transportation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of 1 kg of sodium chloroacetate to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200208, '0d5f96a5-a111-4ff2-9885-7824b39db4d8', 'market for selective coat, copper sheet, physical vapour deposition | selective coat, copper sheet, physical vapour deposition', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''selective coat, copper sheet, physical vapour deposition'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''selective coat, copper sheet, physical vapour deposition'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''selective coat, copper sheet, physical vapour deposition'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200209, '0d6b40e1-60ef-4803-9cac-8ba3ce79adc3', 'treatment of non-sulfidic overburden, off-site | non-sulfidic overburden, off-site', 'The module is designed for unspecific use for disposal of sulphidic tailings in non-ferrous metal extraction. The module includes land use. No rehabilitation is assumed;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200210, '0d7513b3-3f0a-4e74-854c-14ce628f4393', 'market for building, hall, wood construction | building, hall, wood construction', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''building, hall, wood construction'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200211, '0d90ad90-4025-4a89-8ce2-06a084365a3c', 'electric connector production, wire clamp | electric connector, wire clamp', 'This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of clamp connection type connectors for electronics in general. It is based on the assumption that a typical clamp type connector for 3 wires has an average weight of 9.0 g. The data represent a current clamp type connector for three wires used in the electronics industry in general. Material data are taken from datasheets of producers of such capacitors and from the literature. Infrastructure and production efforts are based on own assumptions and taken from the Swedish LCI database and have thus, accordingly higher uncertainty.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From reception of metals and plastics at the factory gate. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This dataset includes raw material input and production efforts for the production of clamp type connectors.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200212, '0d9dd9e7-579e-4fda-800a-1c9bd69e11b1', 'treatment of waste polyethylene, open dump, moist infiltration class (300mm) | waste polyethylene', 'This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of ''waste polyethylene'' in an open dump. Recommended use of this dataset: for PE, which goes to disposal as part of unmanaged communal waste mixture. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% PE. ;Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 41.63 MJ/kg; net heating value 39.01 MJ/kg; H2O 4000; O na; H 140500; C 842870; S 488.02; N 692.75; P na; B na; Cl 1505.3; Br 9.8766; F 14.815; I na; Ag na; As 1.7511; Ba 246.91; Cd 34.962; Co 1.7284; Cr 12.84; Cu 42.605; Hg 0.049383; Mn 30.947; Mo na; Ni 0.98766; Pb 23.272; Sb 10.37; Se 1.9354; Sn 3.9282; V 2271.6; Zn 352.24; Be 0.46081; Sc na; Sr 81.563; Ti 921.61; Tl 0.36864; W na; Si na; Fe 1580.3; Ca 2666.7; Al 184.32; K na; Mg 98.766; Na 1350.6. ;Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 1%. 0.001863 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the uncontrolled disposal location is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open dump are released to air via gas and to water via leachate.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200213, '0da18f74-561e-42c2-9fed-4d2334b7d084', 'market for landed hake, fresh | landed hake, fresh', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''landed hake, fresh'', in the Global geography.;This dataset represents the transport of 1 kg of landed hake from the harbor or port that is landed till the place where it is later sold for commercial or private consumption. No losses are considered in this dataset.;The product ''landed hake, fresh'' is a wild-caught fish landed whole at the port. The activity starts with the reception of landed hake. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the provision of hake for commercial or private consumption.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200214, '0db6f979-f0af-485d-a62d-93125226d22a', 'market for printed wiring board, for power supply unit, desktop computer, Pb containing | printed wiring board, for power supply unit, desktop computer, Pb containing', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''printed wiring board, for power supply unit, desktop computer, Pb containing'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''printed wiring board, for power supply unit, desktop computer, Pb containing'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''printed wiring board, for power supply unit, desktop computer, Pb containing'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200215, '0dc1f59c-9e3e-415b-aba9-48d315e716ba', 'treatment of residue from mechanical treatment, laser printer, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of ''residue from mechanical treatment, laser printer'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: Only for incineration of shredder residues generated in the recycling (mechanical treatment) of laser printersInventoried waste contains several fractions: 1.92% rubber; 47.1% Plastics from electronic consumer goods; 47.1% Plastics from electronic industrial goods; 1.42% MSWI iron scrap; 0.151% Alu in MSW; 2.25% wiring copper; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 34.74 MJ/kg; net heating value 33.3 MJ/kg; H2O 8644.9; O 50262; H 71805; C 784140; S 411.86; N 12537; P 482.64; B na; Cl 6388.1; Br 5188.1; F 235.65; I na; Ag na; As 7.0695; Ba 166.84; Cd 142.06; Co 27.785; Cr 66.493; Cu 25690; Hg 0.80123; Mn 40.518; Mo 2.8278; Ni 487.51; Pb 144.39; Sb 4523; Se 1.8471; Sn 200.84; V 4.2501; Zn 725.91; Be 0.43978; Sc na; Sr 77.842; Ti 4220; Tl 0.35183; W na; Si 3233.4; Fe 13043; Ca 2933.4; Al 3901.8; K 110.28; Mg na; Na 131.49. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 88.9%; Alu: 42.87%; Copper: 88.69%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 6.7022g iron scrap, 0.46441g aluminium scrap, 6.9711g copper scrap. Net energy production: 4.28MJ/kg electric energy and 8.31MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200216, '0de35c48-0843-44dd-9134-96a5873bf10e', 'market for fennel | fennel', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''fennel'', in the Global geography.;In this market, default transport model and expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The default transport distances are built on a generic model which assigns the transport distances based on the ISIC code. This approach is, especially in case of fruits and vegetables, rather coarse. So in a certain cases expert judgement is used to adjust the default distances.;;The transport distances and associated impacts presented in the markets represents the average scenario for given geography. In case of fruits and vegetables the final impact at the consumer vary a lot depending on whether the food is consumed near the producer or far. The average impact of, for example, banana is overestimated if the consumer is present in Brazil and it is heavily underestimated is the consumer is present in Europe. The markets are modelled so, that editing to model concrete scenario is possible and easy.;;Fruits and vegetables are traded all over the world on an increasing scale. ;It is assumed, that all fennels which are transported are being transported by infrastructure equipped for transport of goods in need of atmosphere control.;;The recomended conditions for transport of fennels are (CargoHandbook.com, accessed 20150127); temperature: 0 to +1°C, ventilation: 10 m3/h, humidity (relative): 90 to 95 %, approximate shelf life (in ambient air): 2 weeks.;The product ''fennel'' is a vegetable. It is an annual crop. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''fennel'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''fennel'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are considered.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200217, '0de560ab-e6e4-47d5-95d3-81192ac92ccc', 'ilmenite - magnetite mine operation | magnetite', 'Ilmenite and magnetite mining from hard-rock ore. Based on Tellnes mine (Norway) and Lac Allard mine (Canada).;Comments on modelling. All the flows related to energy consumption are based on U.S. Department of Energy survay from 2007 on Mining Industry (http://www1.eere.energy.gov/manufacturing/industries_technologies/mining/pdfs/mining_bandwidth.pdf). The emissions are based on limestone quarry operation and production datasets. The land use and occupation is based on rough measurements from map. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activities includes both mining operation and beneficiation. This activity includes blasting, all transports within the mine (for mining and recultivation) and the infrastructure. The primary processing is part of the activity as well; crushing, washing, grinding, separation and transportation by conveyor belt.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200218, '0df336a3-e569-4f9b-b6a4-56d8d8c5dfd7', 'market for wood preservative, water-based, outdoor use, no ground contact | wood preservative, water-based, outdoor use, no ground contact', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the global market for organic, water-based wood preservative for outdoor use (no ground contact).Transport distances are based on the ecoinvent Default Transport Assumptions for global transport, accessible at https://www.ecoinvent.org/files/transport_default_20191112.xlsx, based on transport statistics, according to a methodology developed by Borken & Weidema (2013). Activity starts with the product leaving the factory gate, ready for shipment. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Activity ends with the reception of the product at the consuming entity. Average transportation requirements from producer to consuming entity are covered.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200219, '0dfab792-8a7c-40f1-ae89-95f5d4622113', 'market for silicone factory | silicone factory', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''silicone factory'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a silicone factory. The infrastructure is based on average data from two chemical plants, with a yearly production of 1 Mio. tons and its life time is assumed to be 100 years. The process includes land use, machinery and buildings. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200220, '0e226511-83a8-4e86-bcf1-5c21c19720c0', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, industrial device, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, industrial device', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in slag compartment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Bottom ash is the by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''residue from mechanical treatment, industrial device''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''residue from mechanical treatment, industrial device''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200221, '0e361527-f18d-459c-803d-553089f68706', 'market for zinc scrap, post-consumer | zinc scrap, post-consumer', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''zinc scrap, post-consumer'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200222, '0e3c876e-1b15-4817-88df-cea1b1da3ce0', 'continuous dyeing, fibre, cotton | continuous dyeing, fibre, cotton', 'Data collected from mostly vertically integrated mills on a global level. The activity begins with untreated cotton fibres, which are first pre-treated before being dyed, and ends with cotton dyed. It includes electricity use and chemicals. It does not include the cotton fibres. ;Wastewater emissions have been modelled based on primary data and completed with default data, considering wastewater treatment. The activity begins with loading untreated fibre. However, this is service activity. This means that the loaded fibre is not considered as an input of this process. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity delivers the service of dyeing 1kg fibre. It has to be used with 1.04 kg of fibre (taking into account the fibre loss). This dataset represents a mixture of dryed and undryed fibre. This activity is for a fibre with a grammage of 236g/square meter.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200223, '0e672533-b436-43ec-82b5-1c328bccd932', 'market for capacitor, electrolyte type, < 2cm height | capacitor, electrolyte type, < 2cm height', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''capacitor, electrolyte type, < 2cm height'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''capacitor, electrolyte type, < 2cm height'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''capacitor, electrolyte type, < 2cm height'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200224, '0e67a594-83b3-4a2b-891e-a76430bded64', 'market for potato, organic | potato, organic', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''potato, organic'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The product ''potato, organic'' is a root vegetable. It is an annual crop. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''potato, organic'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''potato, organic'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200225, '0e6e3bd2-f7a6-4a5b-9123-003f10d1c9d6', 'market for integrated battery interface system, for Li-ion battery | integrated battery interface system, for Li-ion battery', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''integrated battery interface system, for Li-ion battery'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''integrated battery interface system, for Li-ion battery'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''integrated battery interface system, for Li-ion battery'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200226, '0e77b69b-f84c-4b90-a2ca-78de25c725c0', 'market for lithium carbonate | lithium carbonate', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of 1 kg of lithium carbonate from activities that produce it within the geography of this dataset.;The transport amounts are based on the default transport distances for markets, provided in the ''Default Transport Assumptions'' file available on the ecoinvent website (https://www.ecoinvent.org/support/documents-and-files/documents-and-files.html). See exchange comments for additional details. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce lithium carbonate within the geography of this dataset, with the product ready for transportation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of 1 kg of lithium carbonate to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200227, '0e79380e-524d-4240-bd65-4bb723e46693', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, desktop computer, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, desktop computer', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in slag compartment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Bottom ash is the by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''residue from mechanical treatment, desktop computer''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''residue from mechanical treatment, desktop computer''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200228, '0e88cf13-f592-4e7f-a853-a2108caf9f1d', 'market for heat storage, 2000l | heat storage, 2000l', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''heat storage, 2000l'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the product of a heat storage, a chrome steel tank used with heat exchanger and boiler. It has a volumetric capacity of 2,000 liters. Its production represents all materials necessary to construct it, energy consumption during manufacturing and decommission. The lifetime of the whole solar collector system is assumed at 25 years. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200229, '0e8a7e36-f915-42cb-afcb-390ec4fda2ee', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI-WWT, WW from CRT production, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI-WWT, WW from CRT production', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated from another waste treatment. Bottom ash is generated in the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of sewage sludge (with 70% water) that in turn is generated from wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from CRT production''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from CRT production''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. "CRT" stands for "Cathode-ray tube". The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200230, '0e94a5e1-10c2-4b1c-9bd6-64ba52683d5f', 'market for maintenance, reefer, intermodal shipping container, 40-foot, high-cube | maintenance, reefer, intermodal shipping container, 40-foot, high-cube', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''maintenance, reefer, intermodal shipping container, 40-foot, high-cube'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of maintenance, reefer, intermodal shipping container, 40-foot, high-cube. The service includes the needed materials (steel, synthetic rubber, etc), water, waste and infrastructure. The amount of maintenance might vary depending on what kind of cargo is being transported and how often is the container being used. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200231, '0e9d39bf-83a3-4292-93f2-1d4407471a20', 'palm date production, conditioned and dried | palm date, conditioned and dried', 'This dataset represents 1 kg of palm date fruit conditioned and dried in Tunisia. All the exchanges are calculated per kg of palm date and are based on field data from the main industrial palm date exporter in Tunisia. The inventory includes the following activities: sorting, washing, fumigating, cooling, heating, drying and glucosing. The packaging has not been taking into account.Regarding waste management, palm date kernel are recovered as animal feed. The annual productivity of the plant is 13000 tons of palm dates Deglet Noor (97% of the plam dates are conventionals). The cultivar of the dates studies is Deglet Noor. Tunisia is the world''s largest exporter of Deglet Noor. The activity starts when palm date fruit arrives to the plant in order to be conditioned. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends when the fruit has undergone all processing steps. The palm date is then ready to be packed and send to the importing country. The facility, the infrastructures and the machineries has not been taking into account.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200232, '0eab9ec7-1bf0-4fd5-b1d1-c10cd49b2857', 'market for coal stove, 5-15kW | coal stove, 5-15kW', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''coal stove, 5-15kW'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the product of individual components of a coal stove. The product has a capacity of 5-15 kW and a lifetime of 30 years, that corresponds to 1,600 load hours per year. The process includes all the building necessary materials, the construction efforts, land use and the decommission of all materials. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200233, '0ecc360a-7b9e-4b1b-85de-a29372803ec6', 'market for stirling heat and power co-generation unit, 3kW electrical, wood pellet, future | stirling heat and power co-generation unit, 3kW electrical, wood pellet, future', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''stirling heat and power co-generation unit, 3kW electrical, wood pellet, future'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''stirling heat and power co-generation unit, 3kW electrical, wood pellet, future'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of stirling heat and power co-generation unit, 3kW electrical, wood pellet, future'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200234, '0ed50a40-6af6-4492-9d32-052ccd542a21', 'bronze scrap, post-consumer to generic market for bronze | bronze', 'This activity is linking secondary bronze to the market for primary bronze. This activity is a placeholder. The production volume is set to zero as the activity does not take part into the linking of attributional system models, but it is needed for the consequential system model. The activity starts with the recepetion of post-consumer material From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the virgin material ready for transport', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200235, '0ede0373-77f1-4986-b94d-ff86d8ee4c34', 'market for packing, lime product | packing, lime product', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''packing, lime product'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''packing, lime product''. It represents a process with an annual production volume of 50,000 tons/year and the estimated lifetime of the machines is assumed to be 25 years. The process includes building materials, packing process, loading of the bags on pallets, electricity, waste and machinery. However, the service excludes the input of lime and it should be used alongside 1 kg of it. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200236, '0f17742b-a9d7-47ef-a4a0-653046eb01e6', 'treatment of residues, MSWI-WWT, WW from grass refinery, residual material landfill | residues, MSWI-WWT, WW from grass refinery', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (residues) that is exclusively produced from another waste treatment. Residues are generated in the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of sewage sludge (with 70% water) that in turn is generated from wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from grass refinery''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from grass refinery''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 98.977%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200237, '0f182040-9164-4fc3-894a-6d3860932245', 'onshore petroleum field infrastructure construction | onshore petroleum field infrastructure', 'This activity represents the construction of an onshore production field with 100 wells for extraction of crude petroleum oil. Lifetime 20 years.;For onshore production, several hundred production sites (wells) are summarized to one production field. The inventory is estimated for a field with 100 drilling sites and described in more detail in Schori & Frischknecht (2012) and Jungbluth (2007). Oil and gas processing are done centrally, which requires pipes and pumps.;Onshore production requires space for pumps, separators, tanks, pipes, energy generation (for internal electricity production) as well as cleaning processes (particularly wastewater treatment). In this study a value of 1000 m2/drilling is used.;Meili et al. (2021, section 6.4) assume that the lifetime of the land use change is only 20 instead of the formerly estimated 30 (oil) or 50 (gas) years. This assumption is based on analysis done for horizontal wells in Oklahoma US.;Reference(s): C. Meili, N. Jungbluth, M. Bussa (2021) Life cycle inventories of crude oil and natural gas extraction. ESU-services Ltd. commissioned by the Federal Office for the Environment (FOEN) and the “Verband der Schweizerischen Gasindustrie (VSG), Schaffhausen, Switzerland, DOI: 10.13140/RG.2.2.29142.78409, http://esu-services.ch/data/public-lci-reports/ This activity starts with the transformation of land (forest assumed). From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Materials for construction and energy use for construction. Land use and transformation. Drilling of the wells is not included and hence considered separately. Manufacturing of facilities partly not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200238, '0f2e7877-cccd-490b-a434-a25adccc30a6', 'market for sanforizing, textile | sanforizing, textile', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sanforizing, textile'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is delivering the service of ''sanforizing, textile'' and includes all necessary materials, energy, water, wastewater (produced within the process) and infrastructure in order to process 1 kg of textile. Sanforizing is a mechanical process that treats the textile in order to reduce the shrinkage that can happen during washing. A user should use this service alongside 1.005 kg of textile of their choice. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200239, '0f4b7b53-da34-49d1-9cc3-788e00e327ba', 'market for heat and power co-generation unit, 1MWel, 6.4MWth | heat and power co-generation unit, 1MWel, 6.4MWth', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''heat and power co-generation unit, 1MWel, 6.4MWth'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the production of a heat and power cogeneration unit with a capacity of 1MWel and 6.4 MWth.The process includes building materials, energy consumption and decommission. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200240, '0f57244a-9e2e-4507-80da-e25b31f94da6', 'market for pump station | pump station', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''pump station'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a pump station. The Infrastructure represents a pump station with a capacity of 644,546 m3 per year and a lifetime 70 years. The process include building materials, end-of-life for the infrastructure and land use. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''pump station'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of pump station'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200241, '0f720187-ffc0-443d-a76b-5532d61190de', 'market for beet seed, Swiss integrated production, for sowing | beet seed, Swiss integrated production, for sowing', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''beet seed, Swiss integrated production, for sowing'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;The product ''beet seed, Swiss integrated production, for sowing'' is a seed. It is an annual crop. This seed product is used for plant propagation. The seed produced at the farm is transported to the processing centre, treated (pre-cleaning, cleaning, eventually drying, chemical dressing (for integrated production) and bag filling), stored and afterwards transported to the regional storage centre. Swiss integrated production refers to agriculture meeting the ecological requirements (ökologischer Leistungsnachweis, ÖLN) defined by the Swiss regulation on direct payments to agriculture (Direktzahlungsverordnung). This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''beet seed, Swiss integrated production, for sowing'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of beet seed, Swiss integrated production, for sowing'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200242, '0f829437-f253-4ca8-b887-0e87e1eabd08', 'market for textile, nonwoven polypropylene | textile, nonwoven polypropylene', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of textile, non-woven polypropylene from activities that produce it within the geography of this dataset.;The transport amounts are based on the default transport distances for markets, provided in the ''Default Transport Assumptions'' file available on the ecoinvent website (https://www.ecoinvent.org/support/documents-and-files/documents-and-files.html). See exchange comments for additional details. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce textile, non-woven polypropylene within the geography of this dataset, with the product ready for transportation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of textile, non-woven polypropylene to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200243, '0f99b7c6-d7d7-486a-ac1a-fa8daad367b5', 'market for photovoltaic slanted-roof installation, 3kWp, a-Si, laminated, integrated, on roof | photovoltaic slanted-roof installation, 3kWp, a-Si, laminated, integrated, on roof', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''photovoltaic slanted-roof installation, 3kWp, a-Si, laminated, integrated, on roof'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the installation of a photovoltaic slanted-roof 3kWp, a-Si, laminated, integrated, on roof. The infrastructure has a capacity of 3kWp and a lifetime of 30 years. The process includes all the components for the installation of a photovoltaic plant, energy use for the mounting, and decommission. The solar laminates are integrated in the roof construction and thus replace the normal roof cover. The installation is possible with a simple metal construction for the panels or as solar cells roof tiles. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200244, '0f9db175-10ba-42ec-b990-938e34bc38a4', 'market for furnace, wood chips, softwood storage area, 1000kW | furnace, wood chips, softwood storage area, 1000kW', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''furnace, wood chips, softwood storage area, 1000kW'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the product of a softwood wood chips furnace that includes the storage area. It has a lifetime of 20 years for the furnace the automatic control system, 80 years for the chimney, while its operation time is 2,100 h/year and capacity of 1,000 kW. A furnace of this category is used to produce heat for a local heating network or is often installed in a wood-processing plant in order to be able to usefully utilize the waste produced. The process includes the most important materials used for the fabrication of the furnace, the water storage and the chimney, their decommission, softwood storage and energy used for the construction. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200245, '0fa5723f-282d-4aef-981b-b6a974c17964', 'backlight production, for liquid crystal display | backlight, for liquid crystal display', 'This dataset represents the average production efforts of 1 kg of typical backlight of an LCD screen. It represents all the production efforts of a typical backlight of an LCD screen. Main data are based on information in a US-EPA LCA study about LCD and CRT production. The data represent the respective efforts for backlight unit of a 15inch LCD computer screen, as it is produced in Japan in the late 1990s. Infrastructure are based on assumptions and simplifications and have thus, accordingly higher uncertainties.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From reception of raw materials and auxiliares at the factory gate. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This dataset includes the material and energy efforts as well as the related emissions (air/water) and waste amounts for the production of the cold cathode fluorescent lamp (CCFL), the backlight light guide as well as for the subsequent backlight unit assembly. Estimations for infrastructure are included as well. Packaging material is not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200246, '0fb1feb7-985c-4f73-9cfd-5e3569c4c301', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, WW from tube collector production, sanitary landfill | sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, WW from tube collector production', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively generated from another waste treatment. Sewage sludge is generated in the wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from tube collector production''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from tube collector production''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. Landfill gas capture and utilisation generates 0.03321 kWh of electricity and 0.0599 MJ of useful heat. 0.002598 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to the environment (air due to landfil gas and water due to landfil leachate).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200247, '0fc8a005-8257-4f64-84be-b18b985f320b', 'market for slag landfill | slag landfill', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''slag landfill'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of aslag landfill. The infrastructure consists of a sealed-off slag compartment for bottom ash from municipal solid waste incinerator. Its average waste density is 1,500 kg/m3 and its volumetric capacity of 375,000 m3. The process includes a construction phase of 5 years, a use phase of 30 years and an aftercare phase of 75 years. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200248, '0fcd276b-eb65-4696-8f55-77f1d381d542', 'market for heat pump, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical | heat pump, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''heat pump, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200249, '0fe30904-93df-4993-b1b2-ebc33b52d701', 'market for bottom ash, MSWI, waste plastic, consumer electronics | bottom ash, MSWI, waste plastic, consumer electronics', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''bottom ash, MSWI, waste plastic, consumer electronics'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200250, '0fefaa77-1633-48f0-8869-d4e110b4fff5', 'market for ammonium paratungstate | ammonium paratungstate', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the global market for ammonium paratungstate (APT). It includes estimates for average transport requirements from producing to using entity. APT is the most important intermediate product for all tungsten products. This dataset starts with ammonium paratungstate leaving the gate of the producing entity, ready for distribution to using entities. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the supply ammonium paratungstate to the activities that consume it.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200251, '0ff64fc4-ae6e-459a-aa29-0b16605e1a4d', 'manure, liquid, cattle, Recycled Content cut-off | manure, liquid, cattle', 'From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200252, '10059cbe-e9fa-464c-a78b-3fedc186a336', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT-SLF, waste wood, untreated, municipal incineration | sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT-SLF, waste wood, untreated', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively produced from another waste treatment. Municipal incineration is the controlled combustion of a waste. Sewage sludge with 70% water is generated during wastewater treatement (WWT) of leachate from the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of ''waste wood, untreated''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste wood, untreated''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 98.417%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200253, '1044230d-efe5-4ac3-a00c-ffa0f01fc5b0', 'market for chromium steel removed by drilling, computer numerical controlled | chromium steel removed by drilling, computer numerical controlled', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''chromium steel removed by drilling, computer numerical controlled'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''chromium steel removed by drilling, computer numerical controlled''. Drilling uses a rotating cutting tool (the drill bit) to remove material from the work piece and it predominately uses the front end for cutting. It is applied for shapes like circular cavity or holes. The process is conventional, meaning that it is controlled manually and needs constant supervision. The process is computer numerical controlled, meaning that it operates autonomously once programmed. This dataset represents the drilling of 1 kg of chromium steel. The service includes materials input, production infrastructure, machinery and electricity consumption. Maintenance and tool (bit) replacements are not included. Degreasing is not included and has to be added if necessary. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200254, '1055093b-0cab-4c5c-a5d0-b521bfda8677', 'tinplate scrap, sorted, Recycled Content cut-off | tinplate scrap, sorted', 'From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200255, '10565087-45d5-4407-8b72-5e55273eb4d2', 'treatment of waste graphical paper, unsanitary landfill, very wet infiltration class (1000mm) | waste graphical paper', 'This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of ''waste graphical paper'' in an unsanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: for paper, which goes to disposal as part of managed communal waste mixture. Larger amounts of already separated paper could go to recycling, depending on country-specific situation. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% average paper; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 16.61 MJ/kg; net heating value 14.12 MJ/kg; H2O 110830; O 378670; H 53852; C 404000; S 1406.7; N 3756.6; P 112.95; B 17.19; Cl 1837.5; Br na; F 19.468; I na; Ag 0.047733; As 2.0485; Ba 114.24; Cd 1.6629; Co 0.7359; Cr 14.461; Cu 60.893; Hg 0.13902; Mn 40.221; Mo 4.2976; Ni 9.4431; Pb 80.374; Sb 0.70911; Se 2.5786; Sn na; V na; Zn 124.8; Be 0.97413; Sc na; Sr 58.276; Ti 171.9; Tl 1.719; W na; Si 21255; Fe 1188.4; Ca 3438.1; Al 12391; K 1327.5; Mg 4297.6; Na 918.83. ;Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 100%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 27%. 0.0209 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to air via landfill gas, and to water via leachate.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200256, '105c0151-b043-44bb-b8b6-733d1f5d2b4a', 'treatment of hard coal ash, sanitary landfill | hard coal ash', 'This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of ''hard coal ash'' in a sanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: For small amounts of hard coal ash from small scale furnaces, which go to disposal as part of communal waste mixture. Larger amounts will be landfilled or could be used in building material production. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% hard coal ash small scale; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 0.4712 MJ/kg; H2O na; O 298030; H na; C 100000; S na; N na; P 980; B 350; Cl na; Br 97; F na; I 16.4; Ag na; As 92; Ba 1960; Cd 4.5; Co 49; Cr 192; Cu 146.25; Hg 0.1; Mn 693; Mo 28.5; Ni 194; Pb 376; Sb 9.5; Se 7; Sn 19.8; V 388; Zn 475; Be 19.6; Sc 39.6; Sr 1940; Ti 5880; Tl 9.5; W na; Si 245000; Fe 68600; Ca 19600; Al 166600; K 19600; Mg 58800; Na 9800. Share of carbon in initial waste waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 5%. Landfill gas capture and utilisation generates 0.003793 kWh of electricity and 0.00684 MJ of useful heat. 0.2425 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to the environment (air due to landfil gas, water due to landfil leachate, and subsequent into groundwater).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200257, '10647cfd-a14a-4c77-beab-5c55e0447f26', 'market for titania slag, 85% titanium dioxide | titania slag, 85% titanium dioxide', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This activity represent the market for Titania (or Titanium) slag trade globally.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;"Titania slag, which comes from ilmenite, contains up to 85 per cent titanium dioxide, while rutile contains up to 94 per cent titanium dioxide. The largest application of titanium dioxide is as a white pigment representing between 95 and 98 per cent of worldwide TiO2 consumption. The remaining uses are as a flux for electric welding rods and in certain metallurgical and electronic applications. ;Titanium dioxide is beneficiated by end-users to provide brilliance and opacity to products such as paints, plastics or paper. Manufacturers mainly use rutile in welding rod fluxes as it stabilises the arc and protects the molten metal from oxidation - forming a superior welding joint. In its titanium metal form, it is used extensively in the aerospace and aviation industries because of its lightness, strength and corrosion – and heat-resistance. These properties also make it ideal for use in artificial hip joints, pacemakers and spectacle frames.; The activity includes the transport of 1 kg of Titania (or Titanium) slag traded globally. Transport distances have been taken from the ecoinvent default trasport distances estimates for Basic Precious and other non-ferrous metals From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. It ends with 1 kg of Titania (or Titanium) slag delivered to refinery plant to be further processed.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200258, '106551b7-bda3-4889-9410-3205d5a9c0e5', 'plug production, inlet and outlet, for computer cable | plug, inlet and outlet, for computer cable', 'This dataset represents the production of 1 unit of a typical set of plugs (inlet and outlet) for an electric computer power cord. It is based on a inlet plug (with pins)with a weight of 0.0293 kg and 0.0292 kg for the outlet plug. Main data are based on weighting and calculations of a Swiss type computer cable at EMPA la-boratories, supported by EPD information. ;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From reception of metal and plastic materials at the factory gate. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This dataset includes PVC, HDPE, brass, and copper with their respective manufacturing processes, infrastructure, electricity for the assembly of the plugs, road and rail transportation for input materials from the regional storage to the production site. Water input, emissions and waste are attributed to the electric cable represented in a different dataset.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200259, '106d3e5e-d420-4550-aa45-501b81daa33b', 'market for housing system, cattle, loose, per animal unit | housing system, cattle, loose, per animal unit', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''housing system, cattle, loose, per animal unit'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a housing system, cattle, loose, per animal unit. The infrastructure represents a typical agricultural building for cattle with a cubicle house for dairy cows and rearing to 6 months with the fittings, slurry store, dried roughage store, exercise yard and milking parlour. It has a total size of 22 LU (livestock unit) and a lifetime for the building of 50 years. The process includes the construction materials, building machines, materials for repair and replacement and decommission. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200260, '1075c93f-66d7-441e-ab7c-14216296ed22', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT, WW from concrete production, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively produced from another waste treatment. Municipal incineration is the controlled combustion of a waste. Sewage sludge is generated in the wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from concrete production''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from concrete production''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process are released to the environment (air and water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200261, '10921c10-e954-48ac-8067-e0c9a2cc4520', 'market for zinc | zinc', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''zinc'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''zinc'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''zinc'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200262, '10a3ddde-5d1e-4a3d-8a0b-98f679727063', 'methanol to generic market for solvent for chromatography analysis | solvent for chromatography analysis', 'This process involves the conversion of methanol to the generic market for solvent for chromatography applications. When obtaining chromatography solvent from this generic market, the only driving force for the choice of a solvent will be the market price.;When the use of methanol is mandatory, this will be obtained from the market for methanol. In such case, the user will be accessing a niche market, because it defines specific product features aimed at satisfying specific market needs. When there are no specific product attributes to be fulfilled, these will be satisfied in the generic market. In the generic market the consumption of one product over another wil only be driven by best available price and not by the product attributes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200263, '10cf1b86-0735-48ef-b988-6589c191dbe1', 'market for sodium fluoride | sodium fluoride', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sodium fluoride'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;sodium fluoride'' is an inorganic substance with a CAS no. : 007681-49-4. It is called ''sodium;fluoride'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: FNa. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure and appears as white or colourless crystals. It is modelled as a pure substance. On a consumer level, is used in the following products: textile treatment products and dyes and cosmetics and personal care products. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''sodium fluoride'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''sodium fluoride'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200264, '10db75be-dd82-46c0-92fa-06e0f7d5423a', 'market for sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, heat carrier liquid, 40% C3H8O2 | sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, heat carrier liquid, 40% C3H8O2', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, heat carrier liquid, 40% C3H8O2'', in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200265, '10eeeda4-6316-40e1-b21c-12e7e4bfc21c', 'market for leach residue from copper production | leach residue from copper production', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This dataset represents the global market for leach residue from copper production. It includes estimates for average transport requirements from producing to using entity. This dataset starts with leach residue from copper production leaving the gate of the producing entity, ready for distribution to using entities. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the supply of leach residue from copper production to the activities that consume it.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200266, '10f8c8bf-263b-41c2-8f26-759c4b92b9fc', 'market for carbon black | carbon black', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''carbon black'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;''carbon black'' is an inorganic substance with a CAS no. : 101239-80-9. It is called ''carbon'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure as a black powder. It is modelled as a pure substance. On a consumer level, is used in the following products: inks and toners, adhesives and sealants, coating products, fillers, putties, plasters, modelling clay, textile treatment products and dyes, finger paints, lubricants and greases and cosmetics and personal care products. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''carbon black'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''carbon black'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200267, '11015ad2-7606-4b64-a627-2225fe8dcf49', 'market for sodium borates | sodium borates', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sodium borates'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''sodium borates'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''sodium borates'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200268, '11033d77-2af0-40e9-aeef-2047a74b5c90', 'market for rice, non-basmati | rice, non-basmati', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of 1 kg of ''rice, non-basmati'' from activities that produce it within the geography of GLO. Transportation is included in this market. The transport amounts are based on the default transport distances for markets, provided in the ''Default Transport Assumptions'' file available on the ecoinvent website (https://www.ecoinvent.org/support/documents-and-files/documents-and-files.html). See exchange comments for additional details. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''rice, non-basmati'' within the geography of this dataset, with the product ready for transportation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of 1 kg of ''rice, non-basmati'' to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200269, '1105f207-7c84-4245-b9f4-11edd4b0aa09', 'nutrient supply from manure, liquid, swine | organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N', 'This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''manure, liquid, swine'''' for fertiliser use.;No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use. The purpose of this activity is to connect the chemical production of ''''manure, liquid, swine'''' with its generic uses as fertilizer. The product ''''manure, liquid, swine'''' is connected to the generic market for ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' through this supplying activity. In the agricultural context, ''''manure, liquid, swine'''' can be used directly as a fertilizer input to crop production, eventually with other chemicals; alternatively, a generic input of ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' can be used instead, and this will represent the regional consumption mix for his type of nutrient. A way in between is allowed by using the generic input ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' and link to the activity providing it from a specific chemical.;In all cases, emissions associated to the application of the fertilizer have to be calculated in the crop production activity. This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''manure, liquid, swine'''' for fertiliser use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200270, '110bdc4a-ff9a-44fe-94fd-3c375530a7b4', 'market for heat and power co-generation unit, 200kW electrical, common components for heat+electricity | heat and power co-generation unit, 200kW electrical, common components for heat+electricity', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''heat and power co-generation unit, 200kW electrical, common components for heat+electricity'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the production of a heat and power co-generation unit, with an electrical output of 200 kW. The infrastructure consists of the common components for heat electricity co-generation unit. The process includes all shared components for heat and electricity production and a three-way catalytic converter. The factor of the electrical performance class is derived from the assumed total operating time of 100,000 hours divided by the service life of the components. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200271, '110e0749-beeb-41b6-9b88-eac26ffd2ea7', 'market for nuclear power plant, pressure water reactor, 650MW | nuclear power plant, pressure water reactor, 650MW', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This dataset represents the market of pressure water nuclear plant based on the CANDU technology. ;The CANDU (CANada Deuterium Uranium) technology was used to built this nuclear power plant. This nuclear technology is characterized by the use of heavy water as moderator and natural uranium as fuel. Source: http://www.candu.com/en/home/default.aspx;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a nuclear power plant, pressure water reactor, 650MW. The infrastructure has a lifetime of 30 years. Estimation based on data of the pressure water nuclear power plant in Quebec, Canada. The process includes building materials (steel, copper, titan, aluminium, concrete, asbestos cement, wood and paper, oil, diesel and heating oils etc.), their decommission, energy requirements for the construction and land use. for construction. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200272, '1117f23b-68bd-4bf6-93b1-5c36c0dee190', 'market for control cabinet, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical | control cabinet, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''control cabinet, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW electrical'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the production of a control cabinet, heat and power co-generation unit, 160kW. The size of the control cabinet is 1.8*2*0.6 m3. The infrastructure has a capacity of 160kW and an assumed lifetime 100,000 h. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200273, '113d66b6-8503-43e5-b51b-b594ce22876d', 'intermodal shipping container production, 40-foot | intermodal shipping container, 40-foot', 'This dataset represents production of 40-foot ISO standard container.;The intermodal shipping containers are basically metal boxes which are used for storage and transport of goods. The advantage of using these containers is, that they can be easily transferred from one type of transport to another without the necessity of unloading the goods. ;There are several types and sizes of the containers mainly related to the historical development of intermodal container transport in the given region. There is a continuous effort in the standardization of the container sizes. Below see the table of the different sizes of the intermodal shipping containers as defined by the ISO standard (ISO 6346:1995, ISO 1161:1984, ISO 1496-1:2013). ;The container is designed and constructed for the transportation of general cargo on sea (above and under deck) and on land (road or rail) throughout the world, and will be suitable for the environmental conditions imposed by those modes of transport. All materials used in the construction are able to withstand extreme temperature ranging from -40°C to 70°C without effect on container’s strength and water tightness.;Typical intermodal shipping container. Source: (http://speedlinkltd.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/container.jpg, accessed 20141015).;Data for the life cycle inventory of this container were taken from different sources, primarily from the documentation of different container producers. The main source of information is the technical documentation from Steinecker Containerhandel (Technical Specification for typical 40''x8''x8''6'''' ISO Type Steel Dry Cargo Container, "High Cube", 2012).;Comparison of different container sizes The activity starts when all the individual parts needed for the production of a container enter the assembly site. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends when the container is ready to be used.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200274, '1145a717-5fbe-4867-bbcc-dd01f0349672', 'market for residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, scrap tin sheet | residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, scrap tin sheet', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''residues, MSWI-WWT-SLF, scrap tin sheet'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200275, '114ef7fb-723d-4c40-9b95-159b75772709', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI, steel in car shredder residue, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI, steel in car shredder residue', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in slag compartment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Bottom ash is the by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''steel in car shredder residue''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''steel in car shredder residue''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200276, '11584c48-20e7-4982-9585-0ea000814d00', 'market for potassium hydroxide | potassium hydroxide', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''potassium hydroxide'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;potassium hydroxide'' is an inorganic substance with a CAS no. : 001310-58-3. It is called ''potassium;hydroxide'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: HKO. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure and it has no odour. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. On a consumer level, is used in the following products: washing & cleaning products, coating products, cosmetics and personal care products, pH regulators and water treatment products and perfumes and fragrances. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''potassium hydroxide'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''potassium hydroxide'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200277, '116f2c7d-b65e-4d17-aad1-8688a9015b9f', 'demersal fish to generic market for marine fish | marine fish', 'This is a linking (transfering) activity which links demersal fish, to the generic market for marine fish. Demersal fish includes all non-target fish species that are captured during the fishing of hake. As they have a market value they are linked to the market for marine fish through this linking activity. The activity starts with the reception of landed hake by-catch. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity models the part of demersal fish which contributes to the generic market for marine fish.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200278, '1184def1-6208-416c-b16d-79e99206cbad', 'market for operation, computer, laptop, video mode | operation, computer, laptop, video mode', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''operation, computer, laptop, video mode'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;The ''operation, computer, laptop, video mode'' is delivering the service of operation of a laptop computer in the video mode for one hour of use. The laptop is assumed to have an average electricity consumption of 30W. The operation includes the use of laptop computer and the electricity consumption. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200279, '11878e96-73f7-4cde-8941-1e090b47e901', 'market for diode, glass-, for through-hole mounting | diode, glass-, for through-hole mounting', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''diode, glass-, for through-hole mounting'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''diode, glass-, for through-hole mounting'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''diode, glass-, for through-hole mounting'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200280, '119a56ac-dec7-4c79-820f-778415d19c89', 'market for cast iron removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional | cast iron removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''cast iron removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''cast iron removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional''. Turning is a chipping process where the piece of material is rotating while the cutting tool is not. It can be applied to both inside and outside of the piece to be machined and it is normally used to produce cylindrical shapes. It is performed in metals, wood and plastic materials. When the process is performed with roughing operation, then large amounts of materials are removed at once. The process is conventional, meaning that it is controlled manually and needs constant supervision. This dataset represents the turning of 1 kg of cast iron. The service includes materials input, production infrastructure, machinery and electricity consumption. Degreasing is not included and has to be added if necessary. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200281, '11a1918f-e35d-47fc-a0ec-7c8fa672a672', 'market for hydrocarbons, aromatic, cyclic (C9+) | hydrocarbons, aromatic, cyclic (C9+)', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''hydrocarbons, aromatic, cyclic (C9+)'' in the Global geography.;''hydrocarbons, aromatic, cyclic (C9+)'' is usually not transported and directly consumed on site.;The product ''hydrocarbons, aromatic, cyclic (C9+)'' represents a gaseous mixture of cyclic aromatic hydrocarbon compounds with 9 carbon atoms or more. It can be used in the following applications: chemical synthesis. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce hydrocarbons, aromatic, cyclic (C9+), within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of hydrocarbons, aromatic, cyclic (C9+), to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200282, '11a35304-1c45-41e8-849c-013e5d4bf5fd', 'market for disk drive, CD/DVD, ROM, for laptop computer | disk drive, CD/DVD, ROM, for laptop computer', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''disk drive, CD/DVD, ROM, for laptop computer'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the product of a CD/DVD-ROM drive for a laptop computer. Its production represents a common CD/DVD-ROM drive in the last 3 years before 2005, IDE drive, Toshiba with a total mass of 0.249 kg. Its includes all the materials necessary to construct it, energy consumption during manufacturing. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''disk drive, CD/DVD, ROM, for laptop computer'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''disk drive, CD/DVD, ROM, for laptop computer'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200283, '11a83bde-f6a8-49d3-a822-33c255354a17', 'market for mini CHP plant, common components for heat+electricity | mini CHP plant, common components for heat+electricity', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''mini CHP plant, common components for heat+electricity'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of a mini CHP plant, common components for heat and electricity. The process includes all shared components for heat and electricity production including a three-way catalytic converter, a gas motor and maintenance and planning. The factor of the electrical performance class is derived from the assumed total operating time of 100,000 hours divided by the service life of the components. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200284, '11cec4dc-0897-4464-9f40-1c7c50f30934', 'market for packaging glass, green | packaging glass, green', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''packaging glass, green'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This product is a green glass that is used as a packaging material. Its production can be of virgin input materials or a mix of primary and secondary raw materials. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''packaging glass, green'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''packaging glass, green'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200285, '11e783f5-711c-4f5e-9e4f-0941de8b6b45', 'market for catalytic converter, three-way, 19.1l | catalytic converter, three-way, 19.1l', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''catalytic converter, three-way, 19.1l'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the product of a catalytic converter, three-way. The infrastructure has a capacity of 19.1 liters and weighs 70 kg. Ceramic or, more frequently, metallic (as accounted for here) monoliths are used as substrates, which are coated with the precious metals platinum, palladium, rhodium and various non-precious metal oxides. During production, the catalyst is heated for approx. 5 hours at 300 °C in an electrically heated air stream. This requires 2 kW of electrical power per liter of catalyst volume is required. The lifespan is assumed to be 20''000 operating hours. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200286, '1200be96-7de3-42fe-a7c6-05cb9e2aaa88', 'tris(2,4-ditert-butylphenyl) phosphite production | tris(2,4-ditert-butylphenyl) phosphite', 'This activity produces 1 kg of tris(2,4-ditert-butylphenyl) phosphite production. This product main application is in the plastics and packaging industry, it is used for the production of polymers, adhesives, sealants and coatings (ECHA 2017 and OECD 2009). Tris(2,4-ditert-butylphenyl) phosphite is used as a stabilizer and as an antioxidant (OECD 2009).;Tris(2,4-ditert-butylphenyl) phosphite is usually sold in solid form and close to 100% purity (OECD 2009).;Tris(2,4-ditert-butylphenyl) phosphite is both produced and imported in the European Union (ECHA 2017). ECHA (2017) reports a total consumption between 10 and 100 thousand tonnes. According to OECD SIDS report (2009) in 2002 the global consumption of this product was of 55 thousand tonnes.;Reference(s):;Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de;ECHA 2017. Tris(2,4-ditert-butylphenyl) phosphite. ECHA European Chemicals Agency. Last updated: 14/01/2017 Retrieved from: https://echa.europa.eu/substance-information/-/substanceinfo/100.046.084, accessed 23 February 2017;OECD SIDS 2009. SIDS Initial Assessment Report Agreed at SIAM 18; resubmitted November 2009 SIAP. Retrieved from: http://webnet.oecd.org/Hpv/UI/handler.axd?id=cfda1bb7-ec51-4010-bc84-2cee9dd819ed, accessed 2 February 2017;Maul et al.1993. PROCESS FOR THE PREPARATION OF TRIS(2,4-DITERT-BUTYLPHENYL) PHOSPHITE. United States Patent 5,235,086;For more information on the model please refer to the dedicate ecoinvent report, access it in the Report section of ecoQuery (http://www.ecoinvent.org/login-databases.html) The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Materials entering the process are included as well as energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200287, '12065b74-e8e5-4fa6-bd3a-59a3ad7d6702', 'thermal spraying, cold spray, tungsten carbide-cobalt, on carbon steel substrate | thermal spraying, cold spray, tungsten carbide-cobalt, on carbon steel substrate', 'This activity provides the service of Cold Spray (CS) coating, and it represent the coating of 1 square meter of substrate (carbon steel), with a coating thickness of 150 micrometre. The CS is a process used to for the deposition of micron sized powders. It consist of spraying a ceramic or metallic feedstock powder onto a substrate to build up a coating. This dataset considers a tungsten carbide-cobalt powder to be used. The process is carried out using a carrier gas, which accelerates the powders to a speed which will cause them to adhere the substrate after the impact. This dataset represent a GLO average because it is a well-established technique in the industry. This technique is used because it doesn''t oxidize the coating. The maximum thickness is limited by the plastic deformation of the powder used.;More in detail, the CS works using a gas heather which heats the carrier gas between 800 and 1100˚C. The carrier gas is usually Nitrogen or Helium. A minor part of the gas is kept cold and it pass through the powder feeder and the gas nozzle. ;The dataset is based on direct measures of a pilot plant in the University of Barcelona. It is composed of a robotic arm which operates the spraying gun, the spray gun, the feeder, a compressor, and gas tanks. The dataset includes the energy use of the robotic arm but it does not include the production and the general maintenance of the tooling, of the machine, and of the ancillary equipment.;The CS coating is used when a hard coating is needed, but the application temperature could be an issue (a heat-affected-zone is not accepted), no oxide formation is accepted or a residual compressive stress is wanted. The main industries using CS are aerospace, or biomedical.;References:;Poza, P., & Garrido-Maneiro, M. Á. (2022). Cold-sprayed coatings: Microstructure, mechanical properties, and wear behaviour. Progress in Materials Science, 123, 100839.;Villa, M., Dosta, S., Fernández, J., & Guilemany, J. M. (2012). La proyección fría (CGs): Una alternativa a las tecnologías convencionales de deposición. Revista de Metalurgia, 48(3), 175-191. The activity is a service and it starts with the sandblasted carbon steel workpiece entering the cold spraying cabin. The activity refers to the coating of 1 square meter of substrate for a thickness of 150 micrometer. The carbon steel substrate is not included in the activity exchanges. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity is a service and it ends with the coated workpiece.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200288, '1209e608-379d-4bad-9667-e014c4fe59da', 'transport, helicopter, LTO cycle | transport, helicopter, LTO cycle', 'One take-over and landing of an helikopter.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This dataset describes the energy requirements and emissions of a Landing-and-Take-Over (LTO) Cycle of a helicopter.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200289, '123690d2-856a-4069-987c-023d45ec0a3a', 'gallium, in Bayer liquor from aluminium production | gallium, in Bayer liquor from aluminium production', 'This dataset is designed for accounting for resource depletion in the gallium production. As gallium is assumed to be a by-product of the aluminium production, no upstream burden is allocated to the gallium solved in the bayer liquor. Do not use this dataset for the production of gallium.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] The activity starts with the reception of gallium at the process gate. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This data set describes the simultaneous extraction of gallium together with aluminium in the Bayer process of the aluminium production.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200290, '123ae39a-274e-489b-9d57-6fe0cda6d426', 'celery675 production | celery', 'This dataset represents celery production according to the Integrated Production standard in CH.;Yield: 40 t / ha.;Duration of one cropping cycle: 5.75 months.;Field production.;The LCA study, from which this LCI has been derived, contains detailed descriptions of the system boundaries and the data sources used (Stoessel et al. 2012). The publication is published and freely available with comprehensive supporting information:;http://pubs.acs.org/doi/pdf/10.1021/es2030577;Franziska Stoessel, Ronnie Juraske, Stephan Pfister, Stefanie Hellweg. (2012) Life Cycle Inventory and Carbon and Water FoodPrint of Fruits and Vegetables: Application to a Swiss Retailer. Environmental Science & Technology 6(46) 3253−3262.;;This activity was adapted to include the global average land use change (LUC) emissions according 2nd edition of the Quantis-modified tool developed by Blonk Consultants ''WFLDB-adapted-Blonk 2014 direct-land-use-change-assessment-tool_2015-05-18a.xlsx'', tab. ''Country & land use unknown''. The size of the emission depends on (i) the relative crop expansion in all countries of the crop during the last 20 years and (ii) the corresponding, country specific land transformations. The current results are based on the average FAOSTAT data (harvested area) of 2009-2011 and 1989-1991. The weighted average is used which takes into account relative difference in crop expansion into primary forest, secondary forest, grassland, perennial and annual land. From seedling production. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with harvest and storage. The dataset includes a storage period of 7 months and it''s use of electricity. And the greenhouse heating energy for the seedling production. The pesticide inputs are classified according to their chemical classes and the emmssions are assigned to the soil (100%). Mercury emissions are neglected due to a lack of data while other heavy metal emissions are included. The dataset doesn''t include infrastructure for production and storage facilities. No transports for agricultural means of production from the regional storage to the farm are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200291, '12499b8e-7195-4471-b0e4-b7360c27363a', 'market for road wear emissions, passenger car | road wear emissions, passenger car', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''road wear emissions, passenger car'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200292, '1249e35f-731e-4926-87e5-b10101042578', 'treatment of waste polyethylene, unsanitary landfill, wet infiltration class (500mm) | waste polyethylene', 'This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of ''waste polyethylene'' in an unsanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: for PE, which goes to disposal as part of managed communal waste mixture. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% PE. ;Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 41.63 MJ/kg; net heating value 39.01 MJ/kg; H2O 4000; O na; H 140500; C 842870; S 488.02; N 692.75; P na; B na; Cl 1505.3; Br 9.8766; F 14.815; I na; Ag na; As 1.7511; Ba 246.91; Cd 34.962; Co 1.7284; Cr 12.84; Cu 42.605; Hg 0.049383; Mn 30.947; Mo na; Ni 0.98766; Pb 23.272; Sb 10.37; Se 1.9354; Sn 3.9282; V 2271.6; Zn 352.24; Be 0.46081; Sc na; Sr 81.563; Ti 921.61; Tl 0.36864; W na; Si na; Fe 1580.3; Ca 2666.7; Al 184.32; K na; Mg 98.766; Na 1350.6. ;Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 1%. 0.001773 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to air via landfill gas, and to water via leachate.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200293, '125db934-1e24-4708-af4a-400e1ddd7491', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT, WW from glass production, municipal incineration | electricity, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively produced from another waste treatment. Municipal incineration is the controlled combustion of a waste. Sewage sludge is generated in the wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from glass production''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from glass production''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process are released to the environment (air and water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200294, '126824e5-9574-437a-8524-a385245101e7', 'photovoltaics, electric installation for 570kWp module, open ground | photovoltaics, electric installation for 570kWp module, open ground', 'This dataset represents the production of different components of the electric installation for a 570 kWp photovoltaic power plant namely the fuse box, electric cables, and the electric meter. There is no lighthning protection taken into account. The inverter is modelled in a separate dataset. This dataset starts from the purchase of the needed components for the photovoltaic electric installation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This dataset includes all installations between the panel and the grid, but not the inverter. Process data of the electric equipment include construction materials and wire drawing. The energy use for the manufacturing of the electric installations is only considered with a copper wire drawing process. This dataset includes materials and packaging for the production of cabling and fuse bux. Metal processing is modeled with estimations. The disposal of the product after use is included. This dataset doesn''t include the inverter.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200295, '12772ead-9bd0-44df-887e-49daf07e2ee9', 'wheat seed production, for sowing | wheat seed, for sowing', 'Refers to 1 kg of wheat seed (fresh weight), with a maximum water content of 15%;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] The activity starts after harvest. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The seed is processed in the processing centre, treated (pre-cleaning, cleaning, eventually drying, chemical dressing (for integrated production) and bag filling), stored and afterwards transported to the regional storage centre. No data on wastewater production were available.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200296, '127e9246-02e6-4fce-b4d0-44a8e563417f', 'market for plasticiser, for concrete, based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde | plasticiser, for concrete, based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''plasticiser, for concrete, based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;plasticiser, for concrete, based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde'' is an organic substance which can be added to concrete to make it more flexible, thus increase its plasticity and to decrease its viscosity. Therefore its workability and strength are improved. It is a solid or a low volatility liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure. It is modelled in 14 weight-% water. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''plasticiser, for concrete, based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''plasticiser, for concrete, based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200297, '1288a8ca-aff8-440c-a6aa-2a097acc2279', 'market for acetamide-anillide-compound, unspecified | acetamide-anillide-compound, unspecified', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''acetamide-anillide-compound, unspecified'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;acetamide-anillide-compound, unspecified'' represents an organic substance. The compounds fragment is an acetamide group (amide derived from acetic acid, ethaneamide) and/or an anilide (one hydrogen atom of the amino group replaced with an acyl group) and the molecular formula of the fragment is: -C(=O)NH- (acetamide) and/or (C6H5)NHC(=O)-. The compounds are mostly solid (else liquid) under normal conditions of temperature and pressure. The dataset was modelled from the arithmetic mean of all inputs and outputs of the production of several representing substances. The reference product is modelled to represent a pure substance. On a consumer level, they are used in the following products: herbicides. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of these substances on industrial sites. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''acetamide-anillide-compound, unspecified'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''acetamide-anillide-compound, unspecified'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200298, '1298d402-2666-4ba7-a790-e247f0cc4bdc', 'market for heat and power co-generation unit, 50kW electrical, components for electricity only | heat and power co-generation unit, 50kW electrical, components for electricity only', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''heat and power co-generation unit, 50kW electrical, components for electricity only'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the production of a heat and power co-generation unit, components for electricity only, with an electrical output of 50 kW. The process includes all components related exclusively to electricity production (electric parts, generator 200 kW electrical, and assembly of generator and motor). The factor of the electrical performance class is derived from the assumed total operating time of 100,000 hours divided by the service life of the components. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200299, '12ae75da-f8b0-42bd-86c3-600637398c08', 'market for olive | olive', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''olive'', in the Global geography.;In this market, default transport model and expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The default transport distances are built on a generic model which assigns the transport distances based on the ISIC code. This approach is, especially in case of fruits and vegetables, rather coarse. So in a certain cases expert judgement is used to adjust the default distances.;;The transport distances and associated impacts presented in the markets represents the average scenario for given geography. In case of fruits and vegetables the final impact at the consumer vary a lot depending on whether the food is consumed near the producer or far. The average impact of, for example, banana is overestimated if the consumer is present in Brazil and it is heavily underestimated is the consumer is present in Europe. The markets are modelled so, that editing to model concrete scenario is possible and easy.;;Fruits and vegetables are traded all over the world on an increasing scale. ;It is assumed, that all olives which are transported are being transported by infrastructure equipped for transport of goods in need of atmosphere control.;;The recomended conditions for transport of olives are (Carlos H Crisosto, Elizabeth J Mitcham, Adel A Kader, Department of Pomology, University of California, Davis, CA 95616);;;temperature: +5 to +6 °C;ventilation: 30 to 60 m3/h;humidity (relative): 85 to 90 %;approximate shelf life (in ambient air): 28 to 42 days;;The product ''olive'' is a fruit. It is a perennial crop. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''olive'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''olive'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are considered.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200300, '12b4fdc9-e377-4993-91f5-57711c800387', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT-SLF, waste packaging paper, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively produced from another waste treatment. Municipal incineration is the controlled combustion of a waste. Sewage sludge with 70% water is generated during wastewater treatement (WWT) of leachate from the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of ''waste packaging paper''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste packaging paper''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 96.244%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200301, '12c3c081-43ae-4f48-8f58-541b5b83227f', 'treatment of residues, MSWI, zinc in car shredder residue, residual material landfill | residues, MSWI, zinc in car shredder residue', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in residual material landfill of a waste (residues) that is exclusively produced in another waste treatment. Residues are a by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''zinc in car shredder residue''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''zinc in car shredder residue''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to river water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200302, '12d45b68-cc2e-4e22-963e-0363f69fba2f', 'treatment of copper in car shredder residue, municipal incineration | copper in car shredder residue', 'The process represents the treatment of ''copper in car shredder residue'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: For disposal of rather fine or dusty copper, which goes to incineration as part of Automotive Shredder Residue (ASR). Due to fine grain size of the particles, 50% burnability is assumed, therefore not suited for less fine copper parts in waste. Pure, isolated copper fractions will not be disposed in incinerators, but rather go to recycling.Inventoried waste contains several fractions: 50% Cu in ASR burnable; 50% Cu in ASR inert; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): H2O na; O na; H na; C na; S 0.0000028372; N na; P na; B na; Cl na; Br na; F na; I na; Ag 489.05; As na; Ba na; Cd na; Co na; Cr 2.7346; Cu 924870; Hg na; Mn 1483.2; Mo na; Ni 4062.3; Pb 0.0044823; Sb 3438.1; Se na; Sn 8733.9; V 0.00002178; Zn 1075.5; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si 6428.2; Fe 9181.1; Ca na; Al 40233; K na; Mg na; Na na. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 61.4%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 52.94%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 0g iron scrap, 0g aluminium scrap, 143.36g copper scrap. Net energy production: 0MJ/kg electric energy and 0MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200303, '12e9f2b6-356f-4dcc-8dc7-d7f335b70bea', 'desulfurisation of lignite flue gas | SOx retained, in lignite flue gas desulfurisation', 'This dataset represents the flue gas desulfurisation process of a lignite power plant per 1 kg SOx retained. The efficiency of the desulfurisation is 90%.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] Desulfurisation process starting with the operation of a lignite power plant. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with 1 kg retained SOx resulting from the flue gas desulfurisation process of a coal power plant. The dataset includes the materials. The dataset doesn’t include the waste water emissions and the solid waste and doesn’t include the gypsum as a byproduct. The waste water is used for keeping wet the ash from the operation of the plant and is disposed with the bottom ash and fly ash (Gerhard et al. 1989). 100% of the radioactive elements K-40, Ra-226, Pb-214, Bi-214, Ac-228, Pb-212, Bi-212 and Tl-208 are separated with the bottom ash and fly ash (Merz et al. 1989). References: Gebhard G., Lukas W., Bambauer H.U. (1989) Stabilisierung von Rückständen aus der Braunkohleentschwefelung. In: VGB Kraftwerkstechnik 69, Heft 4, 1989, s.384-392. Merz E., Kroth K., Scholz W., Holzapfel Th. (1989) Radioaktivitätsmessung an Gips aus Rauchgasentschwefelungsanlagen (REA) und Aktivitätsbilanzierung des Rauchgasentschwefelungsprozesses eines mit rheinischer Braunkohle befeuerten Grosskraftwerkes. In: VGB Kraftwerkstechnik 69, Heft 11, s.1114-1118.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200304, '12efc043-5e47-49f2-b4dd-e6d2803c4a11', 'treatment of waste sealing sheet, polyvinylchloride, municipal incineration | waste sealing sheet, polyvinylchloride', 'The process represents the treatment of ''waste sealing sheet, polyvinylchloride'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: For disposal of bulk or small parts of PVC sealing sheet (waste building product)Inventoried waste contains several fractions: 1.7% Glass; 53.9% PVC for sealing sheet; 11% Filler (lime); 33.4% plastiziser; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 23.26 MJ/kg; net heating value 22.53 MJ/kg; H2O 1387.9; O 124680; H 61320; C 477510; S 1000; N 553.8; P na; B na; Cl 249040; Br 38.689; F 8.1246; I na; Ag na; As 1.2205; Ba 103.08; Cd 1.4498; Co 17.46; Cr 28.23; Cu 14.921; Hg 0.47261; Mn 44.17; Mo na; Ni 11.754; Pb 14601; Sb 23.748; Se 1.1607; Sn 205.09; V 159.26; Zn 33.914; Be 0.27635; Sc na; Sr 48.914; Ti 552.7; Tl 0.22108; W na; Si 19305; Fe 2059.2; Ca 45238; Al 110.54; K na; Mg na; Na 1906. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 0g iron scrap, 0g aluminium scrap, 0g copper scrap. Net energy production: 2.58MJ/kg electric energy and 5.66MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200305, '130ed778-1588-4c0b-a372-5c9a17c84bf9', 'market for wastewater treatment facility, capacity 1.1E10l/year | wastewater treatment facility, capacity 1.1E10l/year', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''wastewater treatment facility, capacity 1.1E10l/year'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of wastewater treatment facility with a capacity of 1.1E10 l/year. The infrastructure can be a small size (class 4) wastewaster facultative aereted lagoons treatment facility with a lifetime of 40 years, or it can be a municipal wastewater treatment plant capacity class 2 with an lifetime of 30 years. The process includes building materials, their decommission and land use. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200306, '13241088-8d32-4a51-bd26-a5eb0701cf11', 'octabenzone production | octabenzone', 'Octabenzone is a UV absorber and stabiliser with a pale yellow colour (ChemYQ, n.d. and Dikshith 2013). Octabenzone is suitable to absorb radiation with wavelenght between 240 and 340 nm. Octabenzone is generally suitable for the use in polymers. Octabenzone is flammable and explosive if in contact with air, it therefore needs to be kept in sealed containers is a dry and cool environment (Dikshith 2013).;Reference(s):;Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de;ChemYQ, n.d. [2-hydroxy-4-(octyloxy) phenyl] phenyl-Methanone;2-Hydroxy-4-n-octoxybenzophenone;Ultraviolet absorbent UV-531;2-hydroxy-4-(octyloxy)-benzophenon;2-benzoyl-5-octyloxyphenol;2-hydroxy-4-(n-octyloxy)benzophenone;2-hydroxy-4-(octyloxy)benzophenone. Retrieved from: http://www.chemyq.com/En/xz/xz10/98693mtvnr.htm, accessed 13th of February 2017;Dikshith, T.S.S. 2013. Hazardous Chemicals: Safety Management and global Regulations. CRC Press, Florida, pp. 297;For more information on the model please refer to the dedicate ecoinvent report, access it in the Report section of ecoQuery (http://www.ecoinvent.org/login-databases.html) The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Materials entering the process are included as well as energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200307, '132558dc-fc27-4db9-869d-d72562bf07c4', 'nutrient supply from compost | organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N', 'This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''compost'''' for fertiliser use.;No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use. The purpose of this activity is to connect the chemical production of ''''compost'''' with its generic uses as fertilizer. The product ''''compost'''' is connected to the generic market for ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' through this supplying activity. In the agricultural context, ''''compost'''' can be used directly as a fertilizer input to crop production, eventually with other chemicals; alternatively, a generic input of ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' can be used instead, and this will represent the regional consumption mix for his type of nutrient. A way in between is allowed by using the generic input ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' and link to the activity providing it from a specific chemical.;In all cases, emissions associated to the application of the fertilizer have to be calculated in the crop production activity. This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''compost'''' for fertiliser use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200308, '1354fec9-6820-461e-8a99-d44c4050bbe8', 'treatment of used liquid crystal display module, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of ''used liquid crystal display module'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: Only for incineration of LCD modules (mostly glass and inorganics, some electronic components, copper and plastics) generated in the recycling (mechanical treatment) of LCD screens (Liquid Crystal Display screen residue)Inventoried waste contains several fractions: 0.87% Plastics from electronic consumer goods; 0.87% Plastics from electronic industrial goods; 82% Glass; 0.87% wiring copper; 0.83% liquid crystals; 0.12% ITO coating; 14.5% electronic goods; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 2.835 MJ/kg; net heating value 2.551 MJ/kg; H2O 40144; O 430500; H 7674.6; C 63365; S 102.58; N 1270.5; P 46.362; B 0.0082045; Cl 1519.4; Br 95.711; F 11.587; I na; Ag 30.387; As 0.1305; Ba 8.0249; Cd 10.593; Co 0.51291; Cr 317.5; Cu 26895; Hg 0.16101; Mn 71.044; Mo 0.56082; Ni 1905; Pb 4347.4; Sb 112.38; Se 0.034097; Sn 2351.8; V 0.01305; Zn 2573.8; Be 0.0081182; Sc na; Sr 1.4369; Ti 77.9; Tl 0.0064946; W na; Si 294410; Fe 5671.6; Ca 61772; Al 900.8; K 965.57; Mg 2.0446; Na 52850. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 100%; Alu: 69.8%; Copper: 100%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 3.1892g iron scrap, 0.15979g aluminium scrap, 7.7116g copper scrap. Net energy production: 0.24MJ/kg electric energy and 0.64MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200309, '13562dfb-ea4d-454e-8793-af9472948adb', 'market for bottom ash, MSWI, waste wood, untreated | bottom ash, MSWI, waste wood, untreated', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''bottom ash, MSWI, waste wood, untreated'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200310, '1362f5bc-9ddb-4306-9414-8f53bb09d9a3', 'market for electric connector, peripheral component interconnect buss | electric connector, peripheral component interconnect buss', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''electric connector, peripheral component interconnect buss'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''electric connector, peripheral component interconnect buss'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''electric connector, peripheral component interconnect buss'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200311, '1372b9b8-c543-453d-902d-0440a6f368ca', 'market for barium oxide | barium oxide', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of 1 kg of barium oxide from activities that produce it within the geography of this dataset.;The transport amounts are based on the default transport distances for markets, provided in the ''Default Transport Assumptions'' file available on the ecoinvent website (https://www.ecoinvent.org/support/documents-and-files/documents-and-files.html). See exchange comments for additional details. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce barium oxide within the geography of this dataset, with the product ready for transportation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of 1 kg of barium oxide to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200312, '1377d9e0-7a04-42b3-8b7b-0e2e248fe19e', 'treatment of waste wood, untreated, open burning | waste wood, untreated', 'This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of ''waste wood, untreated'' in uncontrolled, open burning. Recommended use of this dataset: uncontrolled disposal of the waste through burning. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% natural wood . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 15.36 MJ/kg; net heating value 13.99 MJ/kg; H2O 174080; O 372180; H 50163; C 401470; S 125.51; N 986.98; P 108.97; B 2.1107; Cl 330.95; Br na; F 21.106; I na; Ag na; As 0.42213; Ba na; Cd 0.20051; Co 0.086772; Cr 0.65782; Cu 4.1482; Hg 0.31976; Mn 53.118; Mo 0.8302; Ni 0.55581; Pb 27.868; Sb na; Se na; Sn na; V na; Zn 17.807; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si na; Fe 15.479; Ca 130.89; Al 6.3322; K 65.412; Mg 197.56; Na 14.071. Share of carbon in waste that is biogenic 100%. Recycling rates for metallic iron = 0% for metallic aluminium = 0% for metallic copper = 0% . A mass of 0.00757 kg residues are left on ground. The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the uncontrolled disposal location is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open burning are released to the environment (air and soil).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200313, '13838714-e375-4ac9-87e6-7f2a5765046e', 'market for fish oil, from anchovy | fish oil, from anchovy', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''fish oil, from anchovy'', in the Global geography. This is a constrained market for consequential system model, for attributional system models, this is a regular market. In the case of consequential system model, details about the marginal consumer can be found in the comment of the conditional exchange (by-product).;This dataset represents the transport of 1 kg of fish oil from the fish meal and fish oil processing facility to the associated market, i.e. fish oil to generic market for energy feed. No losses are considered in this dataset.;This is a constrained market. The justification for a market constraint is included in the comment field of the conditional exchange. ;Fish oil extracted by pressure from pelagic fish. This oil is rich in Omega-3. The activity starts at the gate of the fish meal and fish oil production facility. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the provision of fish oil to consumers.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200314, '139280e7-0ed7-477b-b97a-d41ab4e8c9c3', 'treatment of waste graphical paper, open dump, moist infiltration class (300mm) | waste graphical paper', 'This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of ''waste graphical paper'' in an open dump. Recommended use of this dataset: uncontrolled disposal of the waste through dumping. Larger amounts of already separated paper could go to recycling, depending on country-specific situation. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% average paper; . ;Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 16.61 MJ/kg; net heating value 14.12 MJ/kg; H2O 110830; O 378670; H 53852; C 404000; S 1406.7; N 3756.6; P 112.95; B 17.19; Cl 1837.5; Br na; F 19.468; I na; Ag 0.047733; As 2.0485; Ba 114.24; Cd 1.6629; Co 0.7359; Cr 14.461; Cu 60.893; Hg 0.13902; Mn 40.221; Mo 4.2976; Ni 9.4431; Pb 80.374; Sb 0.70911; Se 2.5786; Sn na; V na; Zn 124.8; Be 0.97413; Sc na; Sr 58.276; Ti 171.9; Tl 1.719; W na; Si 21255; Fe 1188.4; Ca 3438.1; Al 12391; K 1327.5; Mg 4297.6; Na 918.83. ;Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 100%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 27%. 0.02082 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the uncontrolled disposal location is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open dump are released to air via gas and to water via leachate.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200315, '13990609-1581-4221-9336-7ab79dfe3d18', 'tanker production, for petroleum | tanker, for petroleum', 'The dataset represents the manufacturing and disposal of one tanker for petroelum with a load capacity (DWT) of 36,000 tonnes. End of life is not accounted for other than by the inclusion of materials disposed or recovered for recycling (energy and other requirements for ship dismantling are not included).;The material breakdown of a freight ship is from Jain et al., (2016), which together with the estimated lightweight mass of an average tanker, was used to calculate the tonnage of steel, copper, brass, zinc, machinery, electronics, insulation material, plastics and wood required for ship construction. ;The mass of paint used per lightweight tonne was determined from literature (Kameyama et al., n.d, Harish and Sunil, 2015, Nicolae et al., 2014). Emission of paint and volatiles (NMVOCs) are calculated applying emisison factors from OECD (2009). ;Estimates of electricity, fuels and other consumables (welding wire, carbon dioxide gas etc) required for construction were determined from LCA studies (Kameyama et al., n.d, Nicolae et al., 2014) and an energy efficiency study on shipbuilding (Harish and Sunil, 2015). Welding and cutting demand is estimated by back-calculating from the amount of welding gas consumed, as reported in Harish and Sunil (2015) .;The materials produced at ship end-of-life are included but no energy for dismantling the ship is included. ;The dataset does not include the chemicals, liquids and oils (e.g. lubricants, refigerants etc.) making up a portion of the ship''s weight. Outputs and emissions of liquid materials are thus also not included at end-of-life dismantling of the ship.;References: ;Jain, K., Pruyn, J. and Hopman, J. (2016) Quantitative assessment of material composition of end-of-life ships using onboard documentation, Resources, Conservation and Recycling, 107, pp. 1-9.;Harish, R. and Sunil, S. (2015) Energy Consumption and Conservation in Shipbuilding, International Journal of Innovative Research and Development, 4(7), pp. 26-31;Kameyama, M., Hiraoka, K. and Tauchi, H. (n.d) Study on Life Cycle Impact Assessment for Ships, Energy and Environment Department: Tokyo, Japan.;Nicolae, F., Popa, C. and Beizadae, H. (2014) Applications of Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) in Shipping Industry, 14th International Multidisciplinary Scientific GeoConference.;OECD (2009) OECD Series on Emission Scenario Documents Number 22: Emission Scenario Documents on Coating Industry, OECD: Paris, France Ship production, starting with receiving/obtaining the material inputs required for construction. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the production of one ship. The dataset includes material consumption (steel, copper, plastic, paint etc.), energy consumption (electricity and LPG), welding and cutting, and emissions of the solvent of painting as NMVOC. The dataset does not include the consumption of liquids and oils (e.g. lubricants, refigerants etc.) or energy required for dismantling the ship at end-of-life.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200316, '139f01f5-79c9-47e1-92f6-733570856bba', 'market for sowing | sowing', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''sowing'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''sowing'' on an area of one hectare. It includes the use of diesel powered mobile infrastructure (tractors, machinery). Diesel combustion linearly affects direct emissions. Hence, a user can model the right amount of this service by using information on diesel consumption. For example: If within the user''s model diesel consumption is 30 kg/ha while in this service it is 15 kg/ha, the user can model with 2 ha of this service. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200317, '13b2d211-d706-4cdb-8f69-d426e1c96168', 'market for brass removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional | brass removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''brass removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''brass removed by turning, primarily roughing, conventional''. Turning is a chipping process where the piece of material is rotating while the cutting tool is not. It can be applied to both inside and outside of the piece to be machined and it is normally used to produce cylindrical shapes. It is performed in metals, wood and plastic materials. When the process is performed with roughing operation, then large amounts of materials are removed at once. The process is conventional, meaning that it is controlled manually and needs constant supervision. This dataset represents the turning of 1 kg of brass. The service includes materials input, production infrastructure, machinery and electricity consumption. Degreasing is not included and has to be added if necessary. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200318, '13bde0b4-c0fd-4b68-8c8a-8e234f5a1815', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI-WWT, WW from grass refinery, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI-WWT, WW from grass refinery', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated from another waste treatment. Bottom ash is generated in the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of sewage sludge (with 70% water) that in turn is generated from wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from grass refinery''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from grass refinery''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 98.977%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200319, '13bef2a5-7300-4737-a220-ae721e1705bc', 'vacuum cleaner production | vacuum cleaner', 'This activity represents the production and disposal of an average vacuum cleaner which is approximately 4.45 kg in mass and has a rating of 1400 W. This vacuum cleaner has the envisaged lifetime of 8 years and is manufactured in China. The figures on material inputs from technosphere and energy required to produce an average vaccum cleaner are taken from Gallego-Schmid et al. 2016. The figure on the annual production volume (130000000 units) is calculated from Markets Insider 2017. This activity starts with the reception of materials at the factory. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity includes the processes of material and energy use in manufacturing an average vacuum cleaner. The inventory additionally accounts for disposal of all materials. Packaging is not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200320, '13c248bb-d471-41c6-bf95-9d829e96d457', 'market for fluazifop-butyl | fluazifop-butyl', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for fluazifop-butyl in the Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;Fluazifop-butyl is an organic substance with the CAS no.: 069806-50-4. It is called ''butyl 2-[4-[5-(trifluoromethyl)pyridin-2-yl]oxyphenoxy]propanoate'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C19H20F3NO4. It is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure with a pale brownish color. It is modelled as a pure substance. Fluazifop-butyl is a selective herbicide to control annual and perannial grasses. It is applied post-emergence and inhibits the plant acetyl-CoA carboxylase, which is a subunit in the chloroplasts of many plants. There are no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on industrial sites. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce fluazifop-butyl within the geography of GLO. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of fluazifop-butyl to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200321, '13cc9e60-f1cf-4341-9e8d-9d9d1cb00f9c', 'market for dipropyl amine | dipropyl amine', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''dipropyl amine'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;dipropyl amine'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 000142-84-7. It is called ''N-propylpropan-1-amine'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C6H15N. It is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure with an ammonia-like odour. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: chemicals (as an intermediate). This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''dipropyl amine'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''dipropyl amine'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200322, '13dc3c6b-291e-48ed-8087-61b04aeb2818', 'market for stone groundwood pulp | stone groundwood pulp', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''stone groundwood pulp'', in the Global geography.;This product is generally considered to be used at the production site. Therefore, the market does not contain any transport.;The product “stone groundwood pulp” (SGW) is a type of bleached, mechanical, wood-containing pulp. Mechanical pulp is weaker than chemical pulp (sulfate and sulfite pulp) but has a higher light-scattering coefficients and opacity. For the production of SGW pulp, wood logs are pressed against a rotating grinder stone with simultaneous addition of water. The majority of mechanical pulp is produced at integrated pulp mills which directly process it further into (paper-) products and only a minor part of pulp production is sold on the market. SGW pulp is mainly used for Printing & writing papers and newsprint. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''stone groundwood pulp'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of stone groundwood pulp'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200323, '13dea90c-ac7f-4ce3-96d0-7a7715dc9c69', 'lithium brine inspissation | lithium brine, 6.7 % Li', 'Concentrated lithium brine is base material for lithium carbonate.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This dataset includes the inspissation of lithium containing brine to a concentrated lithium brine by sun energy in the desert of Atacama (Chile)', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200324, '13ec14a6-19df-4e22-bee8-7dfac66f3f66', 'waste plastic, consumer electronics, sorted, Recycled Content cut-off | waste plastic, consumer electronics, sorted', 'From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200325, '13f88c22-e9fc-4bd3-98e5-f7047db13b85', 'market for transport, freight, aircraft, short haul | transport, freight, aircraft, short haul', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''transport, freight, aircraft, short haul'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of transportation of 1 metric ton across the distance of 1 km. This service only considers the transportation of goods. The vehicle operates with kerosene. Its operation is an average flight of a short-haul aircraft for distance between 800 km and 1500 km. The transport node indirectly considers empty trips (if any) by taking into account the total amount of freight transported throughout the lifetime of the mobile infrastructure. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200326, '1406cf0a-18b4-4af7-a66c-ab01188a10b0', 'market for plastic tunnel | plastic tunnel', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''plastic tunnel'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This represents the production of ''plastic tunnel'' measuring one m2. The tunnel is unheated, made out of EVA (ethylene vinyl acetate) and is expected to have a lifetime of 25 years. End-of-life of this product is also accounted for. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''plastic tunnel'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of plastic tunnel'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200327, '140b04fc-3880-46e8-9faf-31426fa8cc49', 'market for acetoacetic acid | acetoacetic acid', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''acetoacetic acid'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;''acetoacetic acid'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 000541-50-4. It is called ''3-oxobutanoic acid'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C4H6O3. It is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. Because of its instability in organic synthesis acetoacetic acid is normally used as ester. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: chemicals, especially as starting materials in the synthesis of intermediates for drugs, dyes, and agrochemicals. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''acetoacetic acid'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''acetoacetic acid'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200328, '14157eaa-9056-4678-8d2e-9b56de5d7e60', 'nutrient supply from potassium chloride sludge | inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O', 'This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''potassium chloride sludge'''' for fertiliser use. ;;No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use. The purpose of this activity is to connect the production of ''''potassium chloride sludge'''' with its generic uses as fertiliser. The product ''''potassium chloride sludge'''' is connected to the generic market for "inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O" through this supplying activity. In the agricultural context, ''''potassium chloride sludge'''' can be used directly as a fertilizer input to crop production, eventually with other chemicals; alternatively, a generic input of "inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O" can be used instead, and this will represent the regional consumption mix for his type of nutrient. A way in between is allowed by using the generic input "inorganic potassium fertiliser, as K2O" and link to the activity providing it from a specific chemical.;; In all cases, emissions associated to the application of the fertilizer have to be calculated in the crop production activity." Activity starting with the application of potassium chloride sludge. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the provision of K-fertiliser.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200329, '1418fef6-3021-4b48-acca-bb7cf7b1639e', 'treatment of residue from mechanical treatment, cathode ray tube display, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of ''residue from mechanical treatment, cathode ray tube display'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: Only for incineration of shredder residues generated in the recycling (mechanical treatment) of CRT screens (Cathode Ray Tube residue)Inventoried waste contains several fractions: 1.84% rubber; 45.2% Plastics from electronic consumer goods; 45.2% Plastics from electronic industrial goods; 2.32% MSWI iron scrap; 2.19% Alu in MSW; 1.39% Glass; 1.86% wiring copper; 0.0715% Pb in ASR inert; 0.0149% silver; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 33.29 MJ/kg; net heating value 31.91 MJ/kg; H2O 8559.9; O 56016; H 68796; C 751290; S 401.89; N 12011; P 470.09; B na; Cl 6229.2; Br 4970.8; F 225.78; I na; Ag 148.56; As 6.7733; Ba 159.85; Cd 136.2; Co 26.621; Cr 79.422; Cu 21842; Hg 0.76766; Mn 61.83; Mo 2.7093; Ni 477.15; Pb 858.09; Sb 4335.5; Se 1.7697; Sn 198.85; V 6.4689; Zn 698.08; Be 0.42136; Sc na; Sr 74.58; Ti 4043.2; Tl 0.33709; W na; Si 8372.8; Fe 20313; Ca 3820; Al 24220; K 105.66; Mg na; Na 1019.8. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 93.18%; Alu: 91.56%; Copper: 86.62%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 10.955g iron scrap, 6.7639g aluminium scrap, 5.7793g copper scrap. Net energy production: 4.09MJ/kg electric energy and 7.95MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200330, '14279650-a12d-4594-8a9f-1731d961b51f', 'pipeline construction, natural gas, long distance, low capacity, onshore | pipeline, natural gas, long distance, low capacity, onshore', 'It is assumed that half of the pipelines are disposed in a discharge at the end of life, the other half stays in the soil. The life time of the pipeline is 40 years.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.] From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This dataset describes the infrastructure needed for a long-distance pipeline onshore with a capacity from average 0.8e6 Sm3/h gas including material requirements, construction and disposal. Helicopter flights for inspection are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200331, '146a2351-24f0-4101-adb2-6444e5d3cb7e', 'treatment of residue from mechanical treatment, desktop computer, municipal incineration | heat, for reuse in municipal waste incineration only', 'The process represents the treatment of ''residue from mechanical treatment, desktop computer'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: Only for incineration of shredder residues generated in the recycling (mechanical treatment) of desktop computersInventoried waste contains several fractions: 1.48% rubber; 36.3% Plastics from electronic consumer goods; 36.3% Plastics from electronic industrial goods; 12.4% MSWI iron scrap; 7.21% Alu in MSW; 2.98% Glass; 2.97% wiring copper; 0.218% Pb in ASR inert; 0.038% silver; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 26.8 MJ/kg; net heating value 25.69 MJ/kg; H2O 7264.1; O 66883; H 55378; C 604750; S 403.51; N 9668.6; P 462.62; B na; Cl 5359.8; Br 4001.2; F 181.74; I na; Ag 379.62; As 5.4522; Ba 128.67; Cd 110.11; Co 21.429; Cr 195.94; Cu 33734; Hg 0.61793; Mn 302.43; Mo 2.1809; Ni 494.62; Pb 2339; Sb 3512; Se 1.4245; Sn 230.6; V 31.526; Zn 584.84; Be 0.33917; Sc na; Sr 60.034; Ti 3254.6; Tl 0.27134; W na; Si 16708; Fe 102190; Ca 4435.6; Al 74799; K 85.054; Mg na; Na 2025.7. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 98.91%; Alu: 96.38%; Copper: 88.81%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 58.603g iron scrap, 22.255g aluminium scrap, 9.2165g copper scrap. Net energy production: 3.22MJ/kg electric energy and 6.37MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200332, '1478ba97-4f55-47a2-9a5f-bd2cc67ddc46', 'market for technical wood drying facility | technical wood drying facility', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''technical wood drying facility'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of technical wood drying facility. The facility includes a kiln with a capacity of 30 m3 wood per charge and a drying time depending on the wood type. The service life is assumed to be 50 years. The process includes land area, building materials, decommission of a kiln, but land used for storage is excluded. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200333, '147a498e-7002-4b13-94a8-226ec395cad0', 'nutrient supply from vinasse, from fermentation of sugarcane | organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N', 'This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''vinasse, from fermentation of sugarcane'''' for fertiliser use.;No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use. The purpose of this activity is to connect the chemical production of ''''vinasse, from fermentation of sugarcane'''' with its generic uses as fertilizer. The product ''''vinasse, from fermentation of sugarcane'''' is connected to the generic market for ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' through this supplying activity. In the agricultural context, ''''vinasse, from fermentation of sugarcane'''' can be used directly as a fertilizer input to crop production, eventually with other chemicals; alternatively, a generic input of ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' can be used instead, and this will represent the regional consumption mix for his type of nutrient. A way in between is allowed by using the generic input ''organic nitrogen fertiliser, as N'' and ''organic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5'' and ''organic potassium fertiliser, as K2O'' and link to the activity providing it from a specific chemical.;In all cases, emissions associated to the application of the fertilizer have to be calculated in the crop production activity. This inventory describes the supply of nutrients from ''''vinasse, from fermentation of sugarcane'''' for fertiliser use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. No machinery expenditures or emissions to the environment are considered related to the actual application of this substance on soil during its agricultural use.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200334, '148f824d-f022-4b7c-a62b-427c08a93135', 'market for thermal spraying, high velocity oxyfuel, tungsten carbide-cobalt, on carbon steel substrate | thermal spraying, high velocity oxyfuel, tungsten carbide-cobalt, on carbon steel substrate', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''thermal spraying, high velocity oxyfuel, tungsten carbide-cobalt, on carbon steel substrate'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is delivering the service of ''thermal spray, high velocity oxyfuel, tungsten carbide-cobalt, on carbon steel substrate''. The High Velocity OxyFuel (HVOF) is a thermal spray coating process which uses the product of the combustion of hydrogen and oxygen to melt and accelerate a feedstock (tungsten carbide-cobalt powder) which is deposited on the substrate (carbon steel). The product represent the coating of 1 square metre of substrate (carbon steel) with a coating thickness of 250 micrometre. The High Velocity OxyFuel process is used in key industries such as oil and gas, power, water, mining, petrochemicals, chemicals, aerospace, paper, engineering, and manufacturing. HVOF coatings can be used as a replacement for environmentally damaging Hard Chrome. This activity starts with the service generation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200335, '14a13f26-6df3-4d4d-be70-20ca8694b848', 'aircraft production, dedicated freight aircraft, very short haul | aircraft, dedicated freight, very short haul', 'The dataset represents the production of a dedicated freight aircraft used for very short haul flights (<800 km). The average very short haul aircraft was calculated from global flight data (OAG, 2016), with 40 different aircraft types used for flights of less than 800 km weighted according to their tonne kms in 2016.;The material composition of the average very short haul aircraft was calculated using data on the operating empty weight (OEW) and the material breakdown (percentage aluminium, titanium, nickel, steel and composite) (both obtained from Cox, Jemiolo & Mutel (2018)). The material breakdown is presented in Cox, Jemiolo & Mutel (2018) as a function of the production year, so the average of the material breakdown for the first and last years of production is applied to calculate the materials for each aircraft. For dedicated freight aircraft the breakdown is approximately: 70% aluminium, 15% composite and 12% steel, with the remained formed from nickle and titanium. The composite material used for aircraft manufacture is modelled in the dataset as carbon fibre reinforced plastic, using the dataset from Cox, Jemiolo and Mutel (2018).;Production data (energy and water) and emissions (VOCs and wastewater) from Airbus’ European manufacturing facilities (Airbus, 2017) are used to model aircraft production, with the Airbus data extrapolated to the average very short haul aircraft using a per seat calculation. I.e. Airbus data on the number and models of airplane deliveries (Airbus, 2016) is used along with the maximum seating capacity of the aircraft models (from Cox, Jemiolo and Mutel (2018) to determine the consumption/emission of materials per aircraft seat, which is then multiplied by the average number of seats in the aircraft of the size-class (determined from the maximum seating capacity of the different aircraft models using data in Cox, Jemiolo and Mutel (2018)). The breakdown of the total energy used in manufacturing into different fuels and electricity is based on data for Airbus internationally (Airbus, 2016).;References:;Airbus (2016) Annual Report 2016. Airbus;Airbus (2017) Blue5 - Sustainable Aviation Industrial Environmental Roadmap: 2017 Status. Airbus;Cox, B., Jemiolo, W. & Mutel, C. (2018) Life cycle assessment of air transport and the Swiss commercial air transport fleet. Transport Research Part D. 58. 1-13;EASA (2009) Survey on the standard weights of passengers and baggage: Final Report. European Aviation Safety Agency;EEA (2017) EMEP/EEA air pollutant emission inventory guidebook 2016 - Update July 2017: Category 1.A.3.a Aviation. European Environmental Agency.;ICAO (2015) ICAO Data+. International Civil Aviation Organization;OAG (2016) OAG Analytics. OAG Aircraft production, starting with receiving/obtaining the material inputs required for construction. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the production of one aircraft. The dataset includes the materials (aluminium, titanium, nickel and composite materials), energy (electricity and heat), kerosene (for aircraft testing) and water used in the production. Emissions of VOCs are also included. Emissions from the production of composite materials are included via an input of carbon fibre reinforced plastic. Electronics and interior materials (plastics, textiles etc.) have not been included due to a lack of available data.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200336, '14b96252-247f-46e2-b9f9-f680245aec50', 'market for aircraft, passenger, very short haul | aircraft, passenger, very short haul', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''aircraft, passenger, very short haul'', in the Global geography.;No transport is considered in this market. Potential initial transfer of the airplain from the production site is neglected.;This product is a mobile infrastructure that is used in the service of transportation. The aircraft is defined as passenger aircraft, representing the infrastructure used to transport only passengers in a passenger flight, while it is capable of travelling trips up to 800 km. It has a lifetime capacity of 671,000,000 metric ton*km and a lifetime distance of 49,000,000 km. The aircraft has an operating empty weight (OEW) of 38.3 tons and each passenger is accounted for 105 kg. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''aircraft, passenger, very short haul'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of aircraft, passenger, very short haul'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200337, '14bf6bd0-c160-4c2b-92fd-515284169301', 'market for furnace, wood chips, softwood storage area, 300kW | furnace, wood chips, softwood storage area, 300kW', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''furnace, wood chips, softwood storage area, 300kW'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the product of a softwood wood chips furnace that includes the storage area. It has a lifetime of 20 years for the furnace the automatic control system, 80 years for the chimney, while its operation time is 2,100 h/year and capacity of 300 kW. A furnace of this capacity is used to heat a large building complex or to supply a smaller heat network.The process includes the most important materials used for the fabrication of the furnace, the water storage and the chimney, their decommission, softwood storage and energy used for the construction. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200338, '14cf236f-ffa5-463b-a876-379074085ff9', 'market for jatropha seed | jatropha seed', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''jatropha seed'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The product ''jatropha seed'' is a seed. It is an annual crop. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''jatropha seed'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''jatropha seed'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200339, '14d40943-d3a9-4fd7-bffb-e34a59fc13eb', 'treatment of bottom ash, MSWI, waste glass, slag compartment | bottom ash, MSWI, waste glass', 'The process represents the treatment of controlled landfilling in slag compartment of a waste (bottom ash) that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. Bottom ash is the by-product that is generated during the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of ''waste glass''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''waste glass''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the slag compartment landfill are released to water (short-term emissions to surface water and long-term emissions to ground water).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200340, '14d4d0a2-95e5-4426-b3e5-8d2ca328c138', 'market for protein feed, 100% crude | protein feed, 100% crude', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''protein feed, 100% crude'', in the the Global geography. This is a generic market; the suppliers of this market make available this generic product by redirecting a part of the production of several more specific products.;No transport or losses have been considered for the generic product supplied in this market, as the transport modelled in the upstream niche markets for the more specific products do already account it.;The product ''protein feed, 100% crude'' represents the protein content of a product that is used as animal feed. Example of products are: soybean meal; skimmed milk, from cow milk; meat and bone meal; cottonseed meal; rape meal; buttermilk, from cow milk. Protein feed is used for animal feeding. Products with more than 20 % of protein are classified as protein feeds. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''protein feed, 100% crude'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of protein feed, 100% crude'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200341, '14d52ba4-ff3a-4483-bbe8-c5899c290b41', 'market for photovoltaic mounting system, for 570kWp open ground module | photovoltaic mounting system, for 570kWp open ground module', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''photovoltaic mounting system, for 570kWp open ground module'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''photovoltaic mounting system, for 570kWp open ground module'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of photovoltaic mounting system, for 570kWp open ground module'', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200342, '150058a4-e042-46a7-99f0-b8ac10478c56', 'market for N,N-dimethylformamide | N,N-dimethylformamide', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''N,N-dimethylformamide'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;''N,N-dimethylformamide'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 000068-12-2. It is called ''N,N-dimethylformamide'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C3H7NO. It is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure and has a light yellow colour. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: laboratory chemicals, adhesives and sealants, coating products, leather treatment products, plant protection products, perfumes and fragrances, pharmaceuticals, polymers and textile treatment products and dyes. This substance is used for the synthesis of other substances (use as intermediate). This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''N,N-dimethylformamide'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''N,N-dimethylformamide'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200343, '15099c2a-5962-43e2-9b4d-f8c12bf0c493', 'market for building, budget hotel | building, budget hotel', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''building, budget hotel'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of building, budget hotel, a touristic accommodation classified as comfort category 3 star. The construction of the infrastructure includes energy and water used in construction, land transformation, building structure and outer building shell. The hotel building has a lifetime of 75 years, while maintenance is included only through the replacement of exchanges with shorter lifetime, like windows with a lifetime of 35 years. The hotel has a capacity between 2,956,500 and 6,460,500 guest nights. Users should consult the specific geography of this infrastructure for more detailed information. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200344, '1516db8c-2d27-438c-8206-e074b24ae501', 'foam glass production, without cullet | foam glass', 'Refers to foam glass of a density of 110 kg/m3 and a thermal conductivity of 0.040 W/mK.;This dataset is based on the dataset for "foam glass production", adjusting the cullet input to zero, with consequences for the input of raw materials (feldspar, lime and soda), the electricity input (for melting) and the CO2 emissions (resulting from decarbonisation of the raw materials), based on data from flatt glass production and "EU commission 2012: Best Available Techniques (BAT) Reference Document for the Manufacture of Glass)" From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. Included processes: melting, forming to a pipe, cooling down, smashing, crushing, mixing with carbon powder. Foaming by heating in a mould, cooling, cutting to slabs and packing. Internal processes (workshop, administration etc.), transport of raw materials and energy carrier for furnace, packing and infrastructure are also included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200345, '15186436-8683-4d0b-b27b-845d41f1ed0e', 'market for computer, desktop, without screen | computer, desktop, without screen', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''computer, desktop, without screen'', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the product of a desktop computer, without screen. Its production represents a typical desktop computer used at home or in an office (Pentium 4, processor speed 2000 MHz, 40 GB RAM HDD, 512 MB working memory, total weight without screen and cardboard packaging 11.3 kg). Computer parts like Graphic card, Network card, Hard disk drive, CD Rom drive, Power supply unit, Printed wiring boards (e.g. motherboard) and batteries are inventoried in individual datasets. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''computer, desktop, without screen'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''computer, desktop, without screen'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200346, '152be4f3-87e9-4cc5-95cb-8fa2cd0f718d', 'market for bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, municipal solid waste | bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, municipal solid waste', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''bottom ash, MSWI-WWT-SLF, municipal solid waste'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:] The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200347, '152d69b9-9cac-4f7f-b26b-a51b83c839d3', 'market for fraction 1 from naphtha separation | fraction 1 from naphtha separation', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''fraction 1 from naphtha separation'', in the Global geography. This is a constrained market for consequential system model, for attributional system models, this is a regular market. In the case of consequential system model, details about the marginal consumer can be found in the comment of the conditional exchange (by-product).;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;fraction 1 from naphtha separation'' describes a mixture of the organic substances cyclopentane and 2,2-dimethylbutane with the CAS numbers : 000287-92-3 and 000075-83-2. They are called ''cyclopentane and 2,2-dimethylbutane'' under IUPAC naming and their molecular formulas are: C5H10 and C6H14. The mixture is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure with a mild, sweet odour. The product is modelled as a mixture. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of these substances on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: chemicals. The activity starts at the factory gate with the product ready for transport. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the product delivered to the consumer.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200348, '153d95da-7911-45e8-a7e2-004610fb89eb', 'market for spoil from hard coal mining | spoil from hard coal mining', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant.;This is the market for ''spoil from hard coal mining'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200349, '15462800-37e1-4a42-aab3-2748a2718f58', 'treatment of spent anion exchange resin from potable water production, municipal incineration | spent anion exchange resin from potable water production', 'The process represents the treatment of ''spent anion exchange resin from potable water production'' in a municipal solid waste incinerator (MSWI). Recommended use of this dataset: disposal of used ion exchange resins *for potable water production*. Resins used of other purifications can have significantly more toxic composition, depending on use.Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% anion exchange resin f. water; . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 16.06 MJ/kg; net heating value 6.081 MJ/kg; H2O 499710; O 70320; H 40160; C 327130; S 23980; N 28640; P 10; B na; Cl 7880; Br na; F na; I na; Ag na; As na; Ba na; Cd 1.592; Co na; Cr na; Cu 16.311; Hg na; Mn na; Mo na; Ni na; Pb 9.2482; Sb na; Se na; Sn 226.21; V na; Zn 34.545; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si 1880; Fe na; Ca na; Al na; K na; Mg na; Na na. Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%.Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%.Recovery of metal scrap from bottom ash to recycling: 0g iron scrap, 0g aluminium scrap, 0g copper scrap. Net energy production: 0.51MJ/kg electric energy and 1.19MJ/kg thermal energy. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the incineration process and auxiliary material consumption for flue gas cleaning are released to the environment (air and water). Infrastructure and waste-specific energy demands for Municipal Solid Waste Incineration (MSWI) and net energy generation are included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200350, '15499fd7-6ff5-4a6f-8bed-e1b813bb8e49', 'market for sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT-SLF, waste glass | sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT-SLF, waste glass', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''sewage sludge, 70% water, WWT-SLF, waste glass'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
