INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200449, '1a829887-6ae7-4497-8ba4-645439389096', 'market for packaging, for fertilisers | packaging, for fertilisers', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset is a market dataset for packaging, for fertilisers, which accounts for the delivery (transportation expenditures) of the packaging to the datasets consuming it. ;The reference product refers to the amount of fertiliser packed, not the amount of packaging material.;Default transportation values are used for plastic products from their production site to the site where they are filled with fertilisers. Default transportation values are used for fertilisers from the site where the packaging is filled with fertilisers till the farm that are finally used. The activity starts right after the production of the packaging, for fertilisers. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the provision of the packaging, for fertilisers, to its users.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200450, '1a9e13f7-241d-420d-b5e3-4a4e2f998c33', 'market for lanthanum-cerium oxide | lanthanum-cerium oxide', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the global market for lanthanum-cerium oxide. It includes estimates for average transport requirements from producing to using entity. Lanthanum-cerium oxide is used in a number of applications, such as in annoys (mischmetal), as a thermal barrier-coating material, and as a semiconductor. This dataset starts with lanthanum-cerium oxide leaving the gate of the producing entity, ready for distribution to using entities. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the supply of lanthanum-cerium oxide to the activities that consume it.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200451, '1ac05810-c5e1-4d42-89fc-d7d3eeae87b6', 'market for aubergine | aubergine', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''aubergine'', in the Global geography.;In this market, default transport model and expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The default transport distances are built on a generic model which assigns the transport distances based on the ISIC code. This approach is, especially in case of fruits and vegetables, rather coarse. So in a certain cases expert judgement is used to adjust the default distances.;;The transport distances and associated impacts presented in the markets represents the average scenario for given geography. In case of fruits and vegetables the final impact at the consumer vary a lot depending on whether the food is consumed near the producer or far. The average impact of, for example, banana is overestimated if the consumer is present in Brazil and it is heavily underestimated is the consumer is present in Europe. The markets are modelled so, that editing to model concrete scenario is possible and easy.;;Fruits and vegetables are traded all over the world on an increasing scale. ;It is assumed, that all aubergines which are transported are being transported by infrastructure equipped for transport of goods in need of atmosphere control.;;The recomended conditions for transport of aubergines are (Hamburg Sud, 2013, Stay cool, We care);;;temperature: +8 to +12 °C;ventilation: 10 to 15 m3/h;humidity (relative): 90 to 95 %;approximate shelf life (in ambient air): 1 to 2 weeks;The product ''aubergine'' is a fruit. It is an annual crop. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''aubergine'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''aubergine'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are considered.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200452, '1ac084d9-8055-4dfa-a61a-856423c12e36', 'market for residues, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, laser printer | residues, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, laser printer', 'This is a market activity, representing a treatment mix. In the case of products needing treatment, market mixes are supplied by the activities treating the product in the geography defined by the market, and they supply the activities needing to treat the product, as they have generated it as a by-product in the Undefined processes (present as a negative input in system models). Transport to the treating facility or losses are also accounted in this type of markets, when relevant. This is the market for ''residues, MSWI, residue from mechanical treatment, laser printer'' in Global geography. Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included. The activity starts with the input from the treatment processes. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. A market for a material for treatment (wastes or recyclables) ends with the provision of treatment, i.e. a mix of treatment providers, to activities that generate the reference product as a waste/by-product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200453, '1aceb709-c188-43b6-8622-4c40aec37dea', 'market for fishmeal, 63-65% protein | fishmeal, 63-65% protein', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This dataset represents the supply of fishmeal, 63-65% protein from activities that produce it within the geography of this dataset.;The transport amounts are based on the default transport distances for markets, provided in the ''Default Transport Assumptions'' file available on the ecoinvent website (https://www.ecoinvent.org/support/documents-and-files/documents-and-files.html). See exchange comments for additional details. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce fishmeal, 63-65% protein within the geography of this dataset, with the product ready for transportation. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of fishmeal, 63-65% protein to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200454, '1acfe229-f9b1-4429-a8cc-6f0fc1320c87', 'market for chemical factory, organics | chemical factory, organics', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''chemical factory, organics'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of chemical factory, organics. The infrastructure is based on information from two chemical plant sites and its lifetime is assumed to be 50 years. This process includes land use, buildings and facilities of an average chemical plant. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200455, '1ae7fd97-43de-4c42-9979-c5498af8385d', 'market for cement factory | cement factory', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''cement factory'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of cement factory. The infrastructure is assumed to have a lifetime of 50 years and a yearly production volume of 340,000 tons. The process includes infrastructure like buildings, paved roads, etc. and the land-use for the cement production, while the rotary kiln is excluded. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200456, '1afda2b0-24c1-4b55-92e5-94facc63809f', 'treatment of sewage sludge, 75% water, WWT, WW from ceramic production, sanitary landfill | electricity, medium voltage', 'The process represents the treatment of a waste (sewage sludge) that is exclusively generated from another waste treatment. Sewage sludge is generated in the wastewater treatment (WWT) of ''wastewater from ceramic production''. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for ''wastewater from ceramic production''. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%. Landfill gas capture and utilisation generates 0.03321 kWh of electricity and 0.0599 MJ of useful heat. 0.002598 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period. The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to the environment (air due to landfil gas and water due to landfil leachate).', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200457, '1b3451ab-e26d-4e1d-82d9-80e631f83f46', 'market for methyl-3-methoxypropionate | methyl-3-methoxypropionate', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''methyl-3-methoxypropionate'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;''methyl-3-methoxypropionate'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 003852-09-3. It is called ''methyl 3-methoxypropanoate'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C5H10O3. It is liquid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. There is no publicly available information about the consumption of this substance on a consumer level. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: semiconductors, photo-chemicals and polymers. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''methyl-3-methoxypropionate'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''methyl-3-methoxypropionate'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200458, '1b3be24e-3d3c-4dc3-9dfa-491daafa606b', 'market for metal working factory | metal working factory', 'This is a market activity. In the case of services or immobile infrastructures, markets are connecting suppliers and consumers at a global level. For specific connections at regional level, direct links between the local producing activities and the local consumers are preferred. Transport or losses are logically not relevant for this type of products.;This is the market for ''metal working factory'', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;This is an immobile infrastructure, representing the construction of metal working factory. The infrastructure is based on average data from several factories. The yearly output is 43,675 tons and its life time is assumed to be 50 years. The process includes buildings, roads and parking spaces on the premises as well as other land occupation. This activity starts with the built infrastructure ready to use. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the infrastructure made accessible to the users. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200459, '1b663e74-6bae-4db4-a006-292d9540233e', 'market for protein pea | protein pea', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''protein pea'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;The product ''protein pea'' is a pulse. It is an annual crop. The ecoinvent database also contains this product from organic and Swiss integrated production. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''protein pea'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''protein pea'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
