INSERT INTO process_info (pcno, pcuuid, pcname, pcdesc, pcsource, createdate, updatedate) VALUES (200461, '1b8721c1-da42-4405-ab72-d0a737cd6d0c', 'market for benzyl alcohol | benzyl alcohol', 'This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for ''benzyl alcohol'', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;benzyl alcohol'' is an organic substance with a CAS no. : 000100-51-6. It is called ''phenylmethanol'' under IUPAC naming and its molecular formula is: C7H8O. It is solid under normal conditions of temperature and pressure with no distinct odour. The substance is modelled as a pure substance. On a consumer level, is used in the following products: washing & cleaning products, coating products, adhesives and sealants and inks and toners. On industrial sites, the substance is used for the manufacture of products in the following sectors: building & construction work. This substance is used for the manufacture of: chemicals, textile, leather or fur, pulp, paper and paper products, rubber products and plastic products. This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce ''benzyl alcohol'', within the geography of Global. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities. This activity ends with the supply of ''benzyl alcohol'', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.', 'ecoinvent v3.10', now(), now());
